title: stuffed beef tenderloin
directions: Defat tenderloin and cut lengthwise about halfway through. Open; salt and pepper.
Rub the inside with garlic.
Saute vegetables in butter.
Stuff inside the meat.
Tie the meat closed with string.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Add the cheese on top. Bake for 5 more minutes or until the cheese has melted.
The meat should be rare to medium-rare.
Garnish with cooked baby carrots and asparagus.
Yields 8 generous portions.

title: icebox fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, Karo, oleo and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in to buttered 1 1/2 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
Delicious!

title: blue cheese bread
directions: Make diagonal cuts in bread.
Mix dressing and butter.
Brush on cut edges.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Heat on grill 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine; press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook squash gently in salted water until barely tender.
Drain well and cool.
Mix eggs, milk, cubed cheese, salt, baking powder, flour, parsley and chilies.
Fold into cooked, cooled squash. Butter a 9 x 13-inch oblong glass baking dish generously. Sprinkle bottom and sides with fine bread crumbs.
Pour in the squash mixture.
Sprinkle more crumbs on top and dot with butter. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 10.
Great leftover!

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, condensed milk, pecans and coconut in large mixing bowl.
Make into small balls and freeze.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate with toothpicks and put on wax paper.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Cook rhubarb in 1 cup water until tender (sauce).
Add sugar, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Add pie filling and cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Put into jars, seal and keep in freezer or refrigerator.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a 9 1/2-inch ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may omit coconut and have an egg custard pie if you prefer.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add 1 can hot, undiluted tomato soup and mix.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Mix with mixer.
Add shrimp and onion.

title: barb's strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients together in electric mixer.
Mix on high for 1 minute. Pour batter into loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg; mix well, then add the other egg.
Mix well.
Add flour slowly; mix as you go.
Add vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Mixture should be stiff. Roll mixture out on waxed paper with a floured rolling pin cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: panetela
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peak.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat to consistency of meringue.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Pour over meringue.
Fold gently, but thoroughly.

title: parmesan pork and penne in tomato sauce
directions: Cook penne to desired doneness on package; drain. Combine bread crumbs and cheese in plastic bag. Add pork. Shake to coat. In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add pork; cook 4 to 6 minutes until brown on each side. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion and oil to pork. Stir gently to mix. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until pork is tender, stirring occasionally. Serve pork over penne.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place fish in a shallow baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread mixture evenly over fillets. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: heavenly white cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, Crisco and egg yolks until yellow. Add remaining ingredients to mixture, alternating the milk and flour.
Beat 3 egg whites until foamy and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
When cool, top with Heavenly Icing.

title: preserving peppers in oil
directions: Cut the peppers in half lengthwise and remove their ribs and seeds.
You can preserve sweet peppers or hot peppers; if you preserve hot, use gloves.
Dry the peppers on a clean towel, then cut them into strips.
Place them in a large bowl, sprinkle with coarse salt and let them drain overnight.
Dry the peppers again. Add the garlic, mint, peppercorns and salt.
Pack them into hot sterilized jars.
Cover completely with olive oil.
Seal immediately.
Keep in a cool place or process in a hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: uncooked chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla, chocolate and salt to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Have ready oats, peanuts butter and nuts.
Add to hot mixture and stir well.
Drop quickly by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Leave until cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add water to desired thickness. Add ground hamburger and sausage. Cook for 1 hour.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Layer half the potatoes, 1/3 the cheese, half of the onions, 1 tablespoon butter, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper;
repeat layering with 1/3 potatoes, 1/3 cheese and remaining onions, butter, flour, salt, thyme and pepper. Place remaining potatoes on top.
Pour milk over.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake until potatoes are tender and liquid is almost absorbed, 20 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Broil until golden, 1 to 2 minutes. (Bake 1 hour and 7 minutes; ready to serve in 1 hour and 22 minutes.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender. Add to spaghetti.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour and sour cream.
Place peaches, cut side down, in pie shell.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer. Serve warm.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pie shell for 10 minutes.
Prick shell with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cook beef and onion until brown, then drain.
Add taco seasoning and cook according to package directions.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chili powder, peppers, soups and enchilada sauce; heat well.
In large casserole, place in layers meat mixture, chips and grated cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Place in a 325° oven until cheese melts and bubbles.
Serves 6.

title: melting moment cookies(my sister's treasured recipe)
directions: Sift together cornstarch, flour and sugar.
Have butter at room temperature.
Blend
into
dry
ingredients until soft dough is formed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with lightly floured fork. Bake in 300° oven 20 to 25
minutes
or
until
edges
are lightly browned. Makes 24.

title: fruitwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and juice.
Spread evenly on crackers.
Top each cracker with slice of fruit, such as star fruit, grapes, kiwi, blueberry or strawberry.

title: french pudding
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Whip cream.
Roll wafers into crumbs.
Place 1/2 of the crumbs in a greased 7 x 12-inch dish, then pour in egg mixture.
Spread over with thawed strawberries. Fold whipped cream over this.
Top with remaining crumbs; top with pecans.
Chill for several hours, or freeze.
If frozen, remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for an hour before serving.

title: date roll
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes, stirring constantly the sugar, dates, butter and eggs.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Cool.
Shape in small ball; roll in coconut.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add butter, sugar and Karo.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Line 8 or 9-inch pastry shell with pecans. Pour in sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: If your religion cannot get you to Sunday School, don't count on it getting you to Heaven.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage and drain.
Put sausage back into the skillet and add the chopped green pepper, onion and celery.
Heat the meat mixture until vegetables begin to soften.
Add real bacon bits, if desired, and set aside.

title: white satin icing
directions: Cook milk and flour together in double boiler until thick. Cover and cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cabbage and carrot casserole(low in calories)
directions: Slice cabbage, onion and pepper very thin. Put the cut cabbage in a top of the stove casserole. Put sliced onion over cabbage, then sliced peppers and a tad more salt.

Top with grated carrots. Dot with oleo (I use squeeze oleo because it is easier). Now add 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil and cook 25 or 30 minutes on very low heat. Be careful and don't let it scorch.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy. Add salt, sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat to blend. Add Karo syrup and vanilla. Beat until mixture stands in peaks.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, mix gelatine with sugar.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatine is dissolved.
With electric mixer, beat in cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed.
Add flour.
Mix together the soda, cream of tartar, milk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Chill dough; cut on very lightly floured cutting surface.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in 8-inch square pan.
Cream sugar and butter until light in small bowl.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well between additions.
Spoon batter over peaches.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour and stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well and spoon into greased casserole dish. Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs, stirring well. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: crispy chicken bites
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Combine flour and seasonings in a plastic bag.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Close bag and shake.
Set aside.
Combine egg and milk in small bowl.
Dip flour coated chicken, 1/4 at a time, into egg/milk mixture and roll in crushed crackers.
Place on large baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with dipping sauce.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar real good.
Mix all flavorings and fold in mixture.
Fold in flour in thirds (1/3 at a time).
Beat egg whites with mixer.
(Do not whip stiff, whip until whites will slide out of bowl all at once in flour-sugar batter).
Heat oven to 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn down to 325° and bake for 1 hour or 1 hour and 20 minutes.
When done, set out for 5 minutes.

title: mississippi strips(sweet and sour pickle)
directions: Wash cucumbers, cut ends off and slice lengthwise in strips. You can use large cucumbers as long as they are not turned yellow in color.
If they have large seeds, cut them out.
An "electric slicing knife" and cutting board works well.
Lay jars on side and pack cucumbers firmly as they will shrink after cooking.
Put 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon mixed pickling spice and 1 teaspoon salt on top of cucumbers in jar.
(This is for quart jar.)

title: tamale joe
directions: Saute meat and onion in a large skillet.
Add seasonings, corn, tomato sauce and milk.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Gradually stir in corn meal.
Add olives; pour into a 3-quart casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar, salt, flour and vanilla.
Beat very good with beater.
Put rhubarb in pie shell; dot with butter or margarine.
Pour egg mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Make sure oven rack is on lower shelf.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vanilla, butter, cinnamon and egg.
Add milk slowly, while stirring.
Add bread cubes and raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Sit in pan of warm water.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool. Serve with cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, refrigerate.
When hardened, cut into squares.

title: fudgy brownies(makes 2 dozen.	fifteen minutes prep.  time)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: red dressing
directions: Beat in mixer just to blend the ingredients together. Refrigerate.
Very good dressing for salads.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare the first 3 flavors of Jell-O separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each. Pour each flavor into an 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm or overnight. Mix pineapple juice and sugar. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot juice. Then add 1/2 cup of cold water. Chill until slightly thickened.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients, except strawberry preserves.
Mold into desired shape (with hands).
I mold into a ring.
Place into refrigerator until chilled.
When ready to serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with biscuit type crackers.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk all at once and stir until dough follows spoon or fork around the bowl. Knead for half a minute. Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: man on the moon cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If batter is too thick, add some water.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Combine with beef consomme and rice in casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rice with browned noodles and garlic
directions: Heat oil in saucepan; add the noodles.
Cook, stirring until browned.
Add the rice and garlic and stir well.
Add the butter, broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover the pan and cook over low heat 17 minutes.
Stir in the chopped parsley.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Take out 1 cup for topping.
Add cinnamon and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Pour into 2 (9 or 10-inch) cake pans.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "scampi-style" shrimp
directions: In a wide frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until boiling. Pat shrimp dry with a paper towel and add to mixture in frying pan.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turns pink (about 5 minutes).
Blend in parsley, lemon peel and Tabasco.
Turn into serving dish.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creole seafood cocktail sauce(for oysters, shrimp, crawfish, etc.)
directions: Mix all ingredients, then mix with your choice of oysters, shrimp or crawfish.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in casserole
directions: Remove skin from split breasts and place in casserole.
Pour soup and sliced mushrooms over chicken.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Ready to serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello (dry) until well blended.
Add yogurt, fold gently.
Add oranges and toss until well blended. Serve over a bed of lettuce with slivered carrots and chopped walnuts.
Delish!

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook together first 3 ingredients in a 4 to 5-quart pot until vegetables are tender.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer for at least 1/2 hour.

title: heavenly brownies(never fail)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Melt chocolate and butter (or margarine) together in large saucepan.
Blend in the sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Spread in well-greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, just until mixture begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift corn meal and flour; measure, mix together and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Stir in onion.
Combine beaten egg and milk and add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir only until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoons into hot fat (365°) and fry until golden brown, turning as necessary.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve at once or keep hot in a slow oven (250°) until served.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well, then press into bottom and up sides of a 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Or use straight sided glass pan.

title: sanders-type frosting
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and shortening until well mixed. Slowly add 2 cups of the confectioners sugar and cream until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until well incorporated and set aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix grape jelly and chili sauce in a medium saucepan.
Simmer on low until mixed well.

title: ham and egg salad
directions: Dice eggs and mix all ingredients.
Moisten with mayonnaise and chill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine butter or margarine, lemon juice, 1 cup sugar and dash of salt.
Beat eggs and egg yolks slightly; stir into lemon mixture.
Cook and stir over low heat, until mixture is boiling.
Chill.
Spread ice cream in a pastry shell; top with lemon mixture and freeze.
Beat egg whites with a dash of salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in lemon peel.
Spread over frozen pie, sealing to pastry.
Bake in extremely hot 500° oven about 3 minutes or just until golden.
Cut in wedges.
Serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. Over hot (not boiling) water, melt 1 cup mint chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add melted mint morsels and vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup mint morsels.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.

title: boneless chicken with rice
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture with the rice, mushrooms and half the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend nuts and water.
Mix into flour and salt.
Add a little more water if needed to hold ball together.
Roll out on floured board.
Place in pie pan and flute edges.

title: tongue pickles
directions: Peel cukes and cut in small pieces.
Be sure the seeds are removed.
Place in enamel pot.
Put spices in a cloth bag and add sugar, salt, vinegar and spices.
Cook until tender and let set overnight.
Heat and can.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute the margarine and onion.
Stir in the flour.
Slowly blend in the milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Heat to boiling; stir often.
Add the broccoli, that has been partially boiled and drained.
Add the cheese.
Serve or let set 2 to 3 hours to blend flavors and reheat.

title: mother's cheese balls
directions: Remove cheese from refrigerator and let warm to room temperature.
Mix cheese and onion with mixer until combined. Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: fabulous cheese dip
directions: Cook meats with onion.
Saute and then drain grease.
Put 2 pounds of cheese in a crock-pot and melt.
Add picante sauce with mushroom soup.
Blend in meat mixture.
Serve warm.

title: creamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip Dream Whip as directed on box.
Blend in sugar and salt. Pour lemon juice over bananas and let this sit for about 2 minutes.
Fold all ingredients together and pour into mold or dish and freeze.
Keeps indefinitely in the freezer.

title: topside-down cake
directions: Stir
cake
mix as directed on package, leaving out 1/4 of the liquid.
Pour into sprayed or greased pan.
Mix sugars and
cocoa and
sprinkle
over
top
of cake batter. Sprinkle chopped pecans on
top of sugar mixture. Slowly pour the cold water over	the mixture and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cut into
squares after
cooling and serve with a spoonful of whipped topping.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Grease two baking pans.
Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Mix eggs, milk, water, salt, pepper and flour together.
Dip tomatoes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
After 10 minutes, turn.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: peppermint hot cocoa
directions: Prepare cocoa mix as directed on package.
Add crushed peppermint candies.
Top with a crown of Reddi-Wip.
Insert peppermint candy stick.
Serve immediately.

title: war time fruit cake
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan, greased and line bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yummy waffles
directions: Mix flour and baking powder and salt.
Add milk, then eggs, which have been beaten.
Add oil last.

title: bran burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil baking pan.
In large bowl, mix together ground beef, egg, salt, garlic, ketchup, 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Divide into 4 balls.
Flatten into 5-inch circle; turn up edges to form 1-inch rim.
Bake 10 minutes.
Combine beans, brown sugar, mustard, mayonnaise, chilies, cumin seed and chili powder. Spoon mixture into meat shells with slotted spoon.
Sprinkle with French onions.
Place strips of cheese over the onions.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes longer.

title: german ice cream torte
directions: Remove rim from 9-inch spring-form pan. Cut brown paper to fit bottom. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Slowly beat in superfine sugar, beating until stiff.
Spread evenly on paper. Bake 50 minutes at 275°. Turn off heat.
Leave meringue in oven 1 hour with door closed.
Remove paper. Return meringue to bottom of pan. Replace rim.

title: pierogies
directions: You will need a 3 or 4-inch round cookie cutter.

title: date balls
directions: Cook for 7 minutes in an iron skillet the sugar, dates, vanilla, eggs and margarine.
Add the nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix together.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut while still warm.

title: raisin bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add syrup.
Add remaining 1/4 cup flour. Stir.
Add salt, vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: potato patties(6 patties)
directions: Combine all ingredients except fat; mix well.
Shape into six patties.
Brown well in hot fat, about 4 minutes on each side.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add chicken broth and cook until desired consistency.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on low for 15 minutes.
Grease baking dish and cover bottom and sides with one layer of crust.
Add chicken and vegetable mixture.
Cover with second layer of crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: tiger stripe fudge
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave for approximately 2 minutes. Stir with spatula occasionally to prevent burning.
Next, melt peanut butter.
Combine white chocolate and peanut butter and spread evenly into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bars. Spoon small amounts of dark chocolate on top of peanut butter and white chocolate mixture.
With a knife, swirl dark chocolate.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Can freeze in Baggies before baking for future use.
Bake for 20 minutes, if frozen.

title: oven steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides.
Salt and pepper.
Cut up peppers and onion.
Arrange on steak.
Add 1 can cream of celery soup. Bake in oven at 400° for about 1 hour.
Can use any kind of steak.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small balls.
Cook at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Top tostada shell with grated cheese.
Put in toaster oven on foil-covered tray.
Toast until cheese melts.
Remove from toaster oven and top with optional items, if desired.
Great as an after-school snack!

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and water to cover in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Drain well. Chop chicken and set aside.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add a layer of corn, half the tomatoes and half the water, onions, green pepper and uncooked beef.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour remaining tomatoes and water over ingredients.
Season to taste. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in the top of a double boiler.
Remove from heat. Pour into a small crock or ceramic bowl.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta omitting butter and salt.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine pasta with tomato and next 9 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: biscuit tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion. Drain.
Mix all other ingredients except biscuits and cheese with drained hamburger meat. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Press biscuits in baking dish for a crust.
Pour hamburger mixture over uncooked biscuits. Top with as much cheese as desired. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until biscuits look browned.
Temperatures may vary.

title: squash melody
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add squash, onion, salt and tomatoes.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chilies and cook 5 minutes more.
Spoon over rice.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix first 4 ingredients; fold in sour cream and mix well. Pour into preheated skillet and bake until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in pecans.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Steam vegetables in a little water for 5 minutes.
Toss with chickpeas.
Mix olive oil and vinegar with salt, pepper and herbs. Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: apple rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and melt together and let cool: Make a regular biscuit dough or take biscuit mix (half of a large box) and mix with water to make a dough (should be stiff).
Roll dough out to 1/4 in. thickness.
Sprinkle with cinnamon then chopped apples and last pecans.
Roll up like a Jelly Roll and cut into 1 inch slices.
Layer in 9 x 13 in. pan.
Pour first mixture over second.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Option: can use only apples or
pecans.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes.
Cook macaroni.
Brown onion in butter.
Brown hamburger.
Add hamburger to onion.
Then add sauce.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in ovenproof bowl.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jewish cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease pan.
Alternate batter and topping, starting with batter and ending with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Stir and refrigerate immediately.

title: fillet of sole with herb butter
directions: Combine seasonings with softened butter.
Refrigerate 8 hours. Spread butter on fillets and bake as usual.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add flour, coconut and pecans. Bake in 9 x 15-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°. Spread jar of marshmallow cream on hot cake when done. Cool, then frost.

title: lime pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices and cover with water and lime and let stand for 24 hours.
Rinse well; cover with clear water.
Let stand for 4 hours.
Drain well.
Heat vinegar, sugar, celery seed, and pickle spice and salt to lukewarm.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Add food coloring.
Bring pickles and mixture to boil for 35 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: snapper with dill sauce(seafood entree)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fillets in a baking dish, skin side down.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend the mayonnaise, mustard and dill.
Brush it evenly over the fish fillets.
Place the fillets in the oven.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until meat flakes when checked with a fork.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and margarine at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add 1 cup powdered sugar and salt. Mix well. Stir in flour. Add water, vanilla and almonds, stirring well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Dredge warm cookies in powdered sugar, if you prefer. Yields 4 dozen.

title: avocado salad
directions: In the blender, combine ingredients and blend until smooth. Taste for seasoning.

title: aunt nez's rolls
directions: Combine in large bowl, 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Add butter.
With mixer on low speed, gradually pour 2 cups hot tap water into dry ingredients.
Add egg, increase speed to medium. Beat 2 minutes.
Beat in 3/4 cup flour or enough to make stiff batter.
Beat 2 minutes with spoon.
Stir approximately 2 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead until smooth (5 minutes).
Place in large greased bowl, cover and let rise approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Cover tight and refrigerate.
Punch down occasionally.

title: crescent tuna melt
directions: Combine mayonnaise, pickle, mustard and onion in a medium bowl.
Stir in tuna.
Unroll dough into 2 rectangles.
Place on ungreased baking sheet with the long sides overlapping 1/2-inch. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Press or roll to form a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spoon tuna mixture in a 2 1/2-inch wide strip lengthwise down the center of dough.
Sprinkle cheese over filling.

title: mashed potato casserole(twice baked)
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a casserole; put in oven on low heat, depending on when you are ready to eat.
This saves mashing the potatoes the last minute. Can also use broccoli.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown onion in shortening; add ground beef and simmer until beef changes color.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, thyme and chili powder.
Stir in tomato paste, tomato juice and catsup.
Arrange alternate layers of meat sauce and noodles (noodles cooked) and cheese in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Bring water to a boil; cook shells 13 minutes. Do not overcook. Cook chicken thoroughly. Save 1 cup of chicken stock. Bring 1 cup stock to boil. Add seasoning package from stuffing mix. Simmer 5 minutes. Add bread crumbs. Cut chicken into small bite-sized pieces. Mix soup with 3 cans milk and slowly bring to a boil. Line baking pan with 1/2 cup of soup. Mix together chicken, stuffing and mayonnaise. Stuff shells with mixture. Lay out in pan and top with remaining soup. Soup will thicken and shells will finish cooking while in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: ramen noodle stew
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then mix next 7 ingredients together and pour over slaw mixture.

title: hershey's snow white mousse pie
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, place 1 cup whipping cream. Stir in gelatin.
Allow to soften at least 5 minutes. Stir in vanilla milk chips.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
(Stir with wire whisk if needed to melt chips completely.)
Chill 15 minutes or just until mixture is lukewarm.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into vanilla mixture.
Pour into crust. Cover and chill until firm.
Just before serving, cover top of pie with chilled cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: super nacho
directions: Season ground beef with taco seasoning and brown.
Spread 1 can Frito bean dip or refried beans on a pizza pan.
Top with ground beef.
Grate Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese and put on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes or until hot in center.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, lettuce.
Serve with chips, tortilla, or corn chips.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In small saucepan melt butter and add stuffing mix. Toss to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup buttered stuffing mix into vegetable mixture.
Turn into 1 quart ungreased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 cup stuffing mix.
Bake uncovered for 35-40 minutes.
Serves 4-6.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: Make an
ice
ring.
Have all liquids cold. Mix them in punch bowl. Add ice ring and serve.

title: herb-coated cod(serves 4)
directions: Place butter in a shallow bowl.
In another bowl, combine the next five ingredients.
Dip fillets in butter, then coat with crumbs.
Place on a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine
concentrates
and add water. Place sherbet and ice cream
in
punch
bowl in small pieces.
Add juice mixture and stir until sherbet and ice cream partially melt.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates in fourths.
Add butter.
Pour boiling water over dates and butter; let cool.
Stir in dry ingredients, egg, vanilla and nuts; mix lightly.
Bake in a large, greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: snicker's bars
directions: Melt
caramels	and chocolate chips, separately (double boilers work
good).
Prepare
x 13 x 2-inch pan; line with waxed
paper.
Place
in order (thin layers): caramels, chocolate and
peanuts.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining melted chocolate chips.
Remove
from pan, wax paper and all.
Place on a
cookie sheet.
Keep in a cool place.
Cut pieces in any size squares.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Mix 1 pint sour cream with soup, salt, pepper and Parmesan. In deep casserole, lightly cover bottom with tablespoons of mixture and Swiss cheese.
Repeat layering, ending with Swiss cheese.
Spread remaining sour cream over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble bread; add remaining ingredients and stir.
Chill.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: country buttercream ribbon chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1/4 cup sugar in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Gradually add 3 tablespoons milk and next 3 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
After chilling, add 5 1/2 ounce can of chow mein noodles.
Serve on lettuce.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices; place in mixing bowl.
Stir in raisins.
Combine egg, milk, pumpkin and melted butter.
Add wet ingredients all at once to sifted mixture, mixing only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full; sprinkle with 2 1/2 tsp. sugar mixed with 1/2 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Cream together egg yolks, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread mixture generously on each slice of bread and roll-up.
Brush rolled bread with 2 sticks of melted margarine.
Then roll each roll-up in cinnamon-sugar mixture (3 tablespoons sugar to 1 tablespoon cinnamon).
Can be frozen at this point.
This recipe fits an 11 x 14-inch pan perfectly.
Take out and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not thaw before baking.
This is a great recipe for Christmas morning.

title: chocolate and peanut butter cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; set aside to cool.
Cream the butter; add sifted powdered sugar, one cup at a time, until blended.
Add vanilla and milk.
You may need to add a little more milk for creamier frosting. Chop peanut butter and chocolate chips together in food processor.
Frost first layer.
Sprinkle with chips.
Add next layer.
Frost whole cake.
Sprinkle chips on top and press chips to sides.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together cocoa, sugar, milk and salt.
Cook until it starts to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add butter and flavoring.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
Butter 8-inch glass dish.
Pour fudge into dish; let cool, then cut into squares.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage leaves in boiling water.
Cover and let stand until leaves are limp, about 10 minutes.
Remove leaves and drain.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Dump everything into crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 9 hours.
The dried apples will almost cook away, leaving a thick gravy with a very good flavor.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until well browned.
Serve with ice cream on top.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Season chops with garlic and pepper.
Fry in cooking oil until done.
Cover with orange juice and sugar; simmer until juice begins sticking to pan.
Serve with choice of garnish and side dishes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon supreme special
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Next add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour in oven.
(This does better if it is beaten a few extra minutes.)

title: one dish cooking vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: la~rues  apple congealed salad
directions: Heat 1 cup juice to boiling and dissolve Jell-O in it. Stir in remaining juice and chill until partially set. Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into a 7 x 13 x 12 Pyrex dish. Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce or plain.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all together with an electric mixer.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Over the top of this, sprinkle 2 or 3 teaspoons of brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour in the remainder of the batter.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan; boil for 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal to mixture.
Stir and drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: low-fat southwestern dip
directions: Mix together and heat thoroughly.
Lightly broil top.
Garnish with green onion slices.
Dip with baked tortilla chips or place in flour tortilla shells.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Pour oil into 9 x 12 inch cake pan.
Cover bottom.
Add cake mix, eggs, and water.
Stir in pan.
Pour chocolate chips on top of cake; as many as will fit.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes. Take out of oven, let stand for 5 - 10 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon, while still warm.
Pour on fudge topping.
Cover whole cake and all of the holes.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions (4-quart pot full) in butter and sugar, stirring constantly until brown (30 minutes or so).
Add beef stock, wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour over toasted croutons and grated Gruyere cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and brown.
Use Swiss if Gruyere is unavailable.

title: southern okra
directions: Cook okra in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Add okra and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: hot doggities
directions: You will need 10 (4 1/2-inch) wood skewers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to boil. Good over chicken or pork.

title: grape-nuts dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Mix in Grape-Nuts and add Cool Whip.
Chill about 1 1/2 hours.
Grape-Nuts will get soft.

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 c. cream of coconut, 1/2 c. rum, oil and eggs.
Beat on medium speed for two minutes.
Stir in pineapple. Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch bundt or tube pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes, cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
With a table knife or skewer, poke holes about 1 inch apart in the cake. The
holes should go almost to the bottom of the cake.
Combine remaining cream of coconut and remaining 2 Tbsp. of rum.
Slowly spoon over cake.
Store in refrigerator.
To garnish use whipped cream, pineapple chunks, maraschino cherries and/or toasted almonds.

title: green bean salad
directions: Steam green beans until tender.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together, except beans.
Shake and pour dressing over beans. Marinate in refrigerator for at least one hour.
Serve chilled.

title: creamed onions
directions: Mix together and heat.
Pour on garlic salt and add a little parsley.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt, then add egg yolks and milk. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and small pat of butter, if desired.
Pour filling into crust and add meringue.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: ham casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Layer 1/2 of noodles, ham and cheese. In a small bowl, combine soup, sour cream, green pepper and onion. Spread half over the top; repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown meat in shortening in skillet.
Add onion, celery and green peppers.
Break uncooked spaghetti into 3-inch pieces and scatter over top of meat and vegetable mixture.
Add seasonings to tomatoes and pour over spaghetti.
Press spaghetti into liquid as much as possible.
Cover and cook about 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: trash
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine.
Pour over 1 big box Chex cereal in Tupperware container.
Cover with lid and shake until all cereal is covered.
Put in trash bag.
Pour in powdered sugar and shake.

title: spicy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers; discard seeds and membranes.
Chop enough of the tops to make 1/2 cup; set aside.
Place peppers, cut side up, in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add the water and cover with vented clear plastic wrap.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 3 to 5 minutes (5 to 7 minutes in low-wattage ovens) or until peppers are barely tender, giving dish a half-turn once.
Drain and set aside.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix flour, meal and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and tear into pieces in crock-pot.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Mix soup, broth, salt, pepper and sage.
Add to bread mixture in crock-pot.
Pour melted oleo over mixture and cook for 2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk; add nutmeg, vanilla, rice and raisins.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in pan of water (1/2 casserole in water).
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and quick oats. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until hard.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute crawfish tails in margarine about 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish tails.
Add basic vegetable mix to margarine and saute for 10 minutes.
Season crawfish and add to mixture along with the soup.
Cook at least 20 minutes.
If too thick, add a little Sauterne wine or water.
Place in pie shell and cover with top. Bake in 300° oven until brown.
Serves 4.

title: loren bush's dish
directions: Cook berries with water and sugar until they pop.
Peel and chop apples in processor.
Pour berries over apples and add red hots and stir.
Bake until apples are tender at 350°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cut bread loaf in half; roll each half into a square. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
In frypan, crumble sausage and add chopped peppers and onion until done.
Drain.
Mix with 3/4 of the beaten eggs.
Put 1/2 the sausage mixture in middle of each square of bread.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top and fold bread up letter style.
Brush sides of bread with remaining egg mixture to seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until done.

title: holiday fondue pot or microwave
directions: Place all ingredients in fondue pot and heat.

Or, to microwave, toss cheeses, flour, mustard and garlic powder together. In a 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole dish, heat wine, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 cup water, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until hot.
Add cheese mixture to liquid.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 7 to 9 minutes, or until cheese is melted, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve with vegetables or bread cubes.
Reheat as needed.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix soup, milk, chicken, potato and peas and carrots.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with chicken mixture with crust.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: old sour
directions: Add salt and pepper to Key lime juice.
Allow to stand at room temperature for 1 or 2 days.
Strain liquid through a fine cloth (cheese cloth).
Bottle tightly and allow to sit for 2 to 4 weeks before using.
Makes 1 cup.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Place baking soda in water.
Add to molasses and mix.
Set aside.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Boil 2 parts water to 1 part vinegar.
Cut peppers in half or quarters.
Place peppers and garlic in sterilized jars.
Pour liquid over peppers and seal.

title: veggie-topped couscous
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil over medium-low heat until crisp-tender.
Stir in carrots, 1/2 cup water, basil, cumin, salt and, if desired, red pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, garbanzo beans and tomatoes.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir together 2 tablespoons water and cornstarch.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.

title: barley casserole
directions: Melt half the butter in skillet and brown barley, stirring constantly.
Saute onions and mushrooms in remaining butter. Combine hot water and bouillon cubes.
Blend all ingredients together, except nuts and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake 30 minutes longer, uncovered.
Before serving, top with grated cheese and place in oven until melted.

title: sundae topping
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut brownies
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and peanut butter. Add peanuts and cereal. Bake in 350° oven 8 minutes in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: pilaf with a difference
directions: Heat oil and margarine in large saucepan with tight fitting lid.
Add pasta; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until golden brown.
Add onion and bulgur.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low and cover. Simmer 20 minutes.
Correct seasoning to taste and serve.
Serves 8 to 10 as a meal and 16 as a side dish.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter, add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Mix in large pan.
Add garlic powder to taste and mix well.
Bake 200° for 1 hour in 2 shallow pans, stirring 3 to 4 times.

title: banana pie
directions: Soak bananas in pineapple and lemon juice for 20 minutes. Drain and save juice. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on bananas. Toss lightly and put in pastry pie shell.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Tear bread in pieces and place in greased baking pan.
Combine eggs and milk, mixing well.
Add egg mixture, onion, celery and seasoning to bread; mix well to evenly coat bread.
Add enough broth to moisten bread thoroughly.
Add oysters and mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: fan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly oil a baking dish big enough to hold the potatoes.
Make several slices 1/4 inch apart lengthwise along potato, stopping 1/4 inch from bottom (a wooden spoon on the cutting board will prevent cutting through the potato).
Heat remaining ingredients until butter melts; brush mixture over potatoes and bake for 1 hour basting every 15 minutes with pan liquid.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Finely chop vegetables in blender or food processor.
Dissolve gelatin in a little of the juice from the draining vegetables. Add to boiling water.
Mix next 5 ingredients with drained vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Use with any type bread.
(I buy unsliced and cut diagonally with crust removed, then into party size sandwiches.)

title: meatballs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix together with a spoon or clean, bare hands until well mixed.
Roll into 1 inch round meatballs. Spray a two-piece broiler pan with nonstick cooking spray.

Place meatballs on broiler pan in a single layer. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until no longer pink inside, turning meatballs over halfway through baking. Serve with tomato sauce over spaghetti or in meatball submarine sandwiches.

title: cereal - peanut bars
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, rice cereal, corn flakes and chocolate chips.
Press into buttered 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut in bars, store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save broth for gravy.
Put deboned chicken in a baking dish.
Pour chicken soup over this and 1/2 can of water or milk.
Fix stuffing according to box directions.
Add to top of the chicken and soup dish.
Bake in 350° oven until browned.
Make gravy by browning flour in a pan; add broth and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Salt and pepper.
You can add any chicken flavoring.
Chicken bouillon cubes or chicken seasoning will make the gravy richer.
Pour over casserole with each serving.

title: lillian's corn soup
directions: Make small roux.
Add onion, shallots, parsley and garlic powder.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on medium to low heat until shrimp are done.

title: chicken of the ritz
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together, stir in chicken pieces.
Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Pour chicken into 9 x 13-inch pan. top with cracker mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: bohemian squares
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg yolks.
Add flour slowly, then vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Place 3/4 of batter in greased and floured cookie sheet.
Add pie filling.
Dab remaining 1/4 batter on top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in casserole dish.
Pour chicken broth over rice. Lay chicken breasts over rice.
Pour cream of chicken soup over ingredients; sprinkle onion mix over ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover during first hour.

title: bar-b-q spareribs
directions: Make a sauce with all ingredients, except the spareribs and the onions.
Sprinkle the spareribs with salt and pepper. Cover with onions.
Pour the sauce over the spareribs.
Cover and
bake 1
hours at 350°.
Turn ribs once or twice and baste occasionally.

title: almond roca
directions: Mix sugar, butter, water, and salt in saucepan.
Stir constantly until hard crack stage.
Pour onto buttered pan. Cover with chips and spread with pastry brush.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Cool.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, basil, garlic, salt and pepper; set aside. Place carrots, bell pepper, celery, onion and water in medium saucepan.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce on bottom of 9 x 13 x 3-inch deep pan.
Place 4 lasagna noodles in pan, overlapping slightly.
Spread 2/3 cup of Ricotta cheese mixture evenly over noodles.
Spread 1 cup of sauce over cheese, then add 1 cup vegetables, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1 1/3 cups spinach leaves, 1/2 cup water chestnuts and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top this layer with 4 more lasagna noodles.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (100°).
Combine milk, sugar and shortening; add salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast and egg. Gradually stir in flour; mix until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Roll on floured surface until very thin.
Cut into shapes with a knife and deep fry in fat* until golden brown.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Turn pumpkin into saucepan.
Cook over direct heat 10 minutes or until somewhat dry or caramelized, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend sugar, salt and spices.
Stir beaten eggs into hot pumpkin; add evaporated milk.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°, then reduce heat to slow 300° and continue baking for approximately 45 minutes or longer until pumpkin is done.

title: caramel-chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecan pieces in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle in chocolate pieces and drizzle in caramel topping.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs; beat on low speed just until combined.
Pour over caramel topping in crust.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool.
Chill covered for at least 1 hour before serving.
Sift cocoa powder over pie, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: squash dish
directions: Slice squash and chopped onions with other ingredients, mixing it into a level pan of water. Cook for 2 hours on medium heat. Heat until it is at frying stage.

title: hot 'n spicy stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornstarch and water in slow cooking pot.
Stir well to blend.
Cover and cook at setting number 3 (low) for 7 to 9 hours or at setting number 5 (high) for 3 to 4 hours until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Stir until dissolved.
Put strawberries in, stir, place on top of Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan. Mix cake mix with the rest of the ingredients. Pour in pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hungry man meal
directions: In a large casserole dish, brown the beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add the green beans, corn or mixed vegetables (or use 1 can lima beans).
Drain juices from canned vegetables and the tomato soup.
Layer and top with the potatoes with 1 egg mixed in well. After layering all ingredients, mixture should have a layer cake look.
Put dish in a 350° oven and bake for 20 minutes until potatoes are a little browned.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, celery and onion.
Drain.
Combine soup mix, rice, broth and water.
Add sausage mixture and blend well. Place in casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix together ingredients.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Put caramel icing on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly. Put into loaf pan, cover with bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over all 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce. Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place evenly into well-greased Bundt pan.
To the remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture, add enough sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to total 1 1/2 cups.
Add margarine and cook until it boils. Pour over bread and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind green tomatoes, onions and red peppers the night before and add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and cover with vinegar. In cheesecloth, put mustard seed, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Add sugar and bring to boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Seal in jars.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: bean bake
directions: In skillet, lightly brown hot dogs with onion, butter, mustard, allspice and pepper.
Pour beans into baking dish.
Add catsup and brown sugar, mixing well.
Spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Layer hot dog mixture over beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayo, milk, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and cinnamon in a small bowl; beat until smooth.
Stir in celery and raisins.
Add more milk until mixture is dripping consistency. Chill, covered, for 2 hours.
Brush apple wedges with lemon juice. Sprinkle dip with walnuts.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9x 2-inch.
Spread pecans on pan.
Heat sugar and margarine to boiling in 1 quart pan, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, 7 minutes. Immediately spread mixture over pecans in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot mixture.
Place cookie sheet over pan until chocolate chips are melted.
Spread melted chocolate over candy.
Cut into about 1/2-inch squares while hot.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together and bake in sheet pan for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: sinful salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine gelatin and water; stir until completely dissolved.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients, except sour cream.
Divide in half.
Pour half the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Keep remaining gelatin at room temperature.
When first half is set, spread sour cream over it. Pour on remaining gelatine.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.

title: pralines(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and Karo syrup in heavy 3-quart pan. Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until cool. Add pecan halves and drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
When firm, store.

title: grandma leonard's orange fluff
directions: Make jello according to package and mix in Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Then fold in mandarin oranges.
Let it set a while.

title: spicy chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Tabasco. Add Italian dressing.
Cover chicken well.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Place in baking dish and bake at 400° until brown.

title: low cholesterol gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 8 to 9-inch square pan; set aside.
In bowl, mix beaten egg, sugar, oil and molasses; then boiling water.
Sift together flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into liquid ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan and bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes. Cool 5 minutes in pan, then cut and serve.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, salt, baking powder, vanilla and flour, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Form into 2 logs. If too soft to work with, put in refrigerator for awhile.
(You can mix chopped nuts, if desired.)
Chill well before slicing about 1/3-inch thick. Bake at 350° until slightly brown on ungreased cookie sheet. Do not overcook.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
These are good iced with frosting the color of the holiday.

title: mother roberds syrup cake
directions: Beat together egg, sugar and shortening.
Add syrup.
Sift together soda and salt.
Add gradually, beating until smooth, then add 1/3 cup hot water.
Bake at 325° until set to touch.
Can be one large cake or cupcakes.
May be iced, if desired.

title: ring of fire hot sauce
directions: Cut up peppers real fine.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over peppers.
Cook in large cooking pan until peppers are done.
Pour in pint jars and seal.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and one stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream other stick with sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high, 15 minutes (it will turn white).
Spread on crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Layer pineapple followed by strawberries. Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Combine rest of cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and 1 cup cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add milk and flavorings at low.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes. Top with pie filling, if desired.

title: barbs' kringle
directions: Work flour and oleo like pie crust.
Add sour cream and form into roll.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 4 portions and then roll into rectangle.

title: amish red-raspberry cream pie
directions: Mix together, roll out and place into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle shell with powdered sugar while hot.
Makes double crust.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/2 package taco seasoning mix and mayonnaise.
Spread into Pyrex dish.
Put 1/2 bottle of taco sauce over this.
Cook ground beef with the other 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix.
Spread on top of first mixture.
On top of this, put lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Put other 1/2 bottle of taco sauce over this.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together the eggs, soup and milk.
Place 2 buttered slices of bread at the bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole.
Lay slice of cheese on each, then half of the shrimp.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Make another similar layer, then end with bread and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes until brown and puffy.

title: no mess brisket
directions: Spread several drops of liquid smoke on top of brisket.
Place brisket in electric roaster or large covered roasting pan.
Pour in can of Cola and roast at 300° for 6 hours.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburg and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Church recipe, makes 5 gallons.
Serves 80.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown first 8 items.
Simmer till thick.
Add chopped olives. Cook noodles as directed on box.
Make 3 layers, alternate noodles, mozzarella, ricotta, meat sauce and parmesan cheese.
Ending with meat sauce and parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bring fruit and 1 cup sugar to a boil.
Mix remaining sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour on top of margarine and spoon on fruit mixture. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine beef, onions and seasoning in skillet and cook until onions are transparent.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mix together.
Remove from heat, peel and slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes and meat mixture in greased casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and cover with cheese.
Return to oven and melt the cheese.

title: boston creme candy
directions: In a saucepan, mix all ingredients except vanilla and pecans. Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Beat by hand until hard.
Pour into buttered pan.
Slice when cool.

title: barbecue style baked beans
directions: Rinse beans; mix together beans and cold water in a 4-quart saucepan.
Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add hot water.
Cover and boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 hour; drain, reserving liquid.
Mix together all ingredients and 1 cup reserved liquid in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° in oven, stirring occasionally, 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until almost all liquid is absorbed.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in an ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package using milk.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
In bottom of a 2-quart baking dish, layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Repeat, ending with pudding. Spread remaining whipped topping on top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: In frypan, mix cream cheese and cooked chicken.
Melt together.
Undo the crescent rolls and put a spoonful of chicken on each roll.
Roll up as usual.
Roll in melted butter and roll in fine crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve with chicken gravy.
May be served with any rice dish.
They freeze well.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo
and
Crisco;
add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, 1
at
a
time.
Alternately add flour and baking powder along with milk and vanilla.
Beat well, put in a tube pan and bake at 350°
until
done
when
a	toothpick comes out clean (about 1 hour and 15 minutes).

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over fresh pork spareribs. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook until tender.

title: south-of-the-border dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spoon mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread yogurt over bean mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Yields about 5 1/2 cups.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Sprinkle this over cake and swirl with a fork.	Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In a large frypan, melt butter.
Fry chicken for 4 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken from pan. Remove grease.
In a bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Place chicken back in pan. Pour sauce over and cook on medium-low heat for 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: country-fried chicken
directions: Blend egg and milk.
Combine flour and seasonings in plastic paper bag.
Shake chicken in bag, dip in egg and milk and shake again.

title: peanut butter and oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Stir in rolled oats and set aside.
Cream together the sugars, margarine and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Chill for 2 hours.
Form dough into
walnut-size balls and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do no overbake.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: banana and raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand until moisture is absorbed. Drop small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in blender.
Dissolve sugar and jello in hot water.
Add mixture to blender and puree.
Add chopped orange and puree.
Remove mixture from blender and mix in other ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: white mice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into oblong pieces, a little shorter than a finger.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Put cooled potatoes in a bowl.
Combine milk and flour in blender until smooth.
Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add milk and flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Add rest except cheese, then over low heat add cheese and thicken.
Put in lightly buttered casserole dish.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix in a saucepan the sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring, until thick.
(You may need to add a tiny bit more flour.)
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: old fashioned oklahoma style ice cream
directions: *Or can use one 14 ounce can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello according to package and let almost congeal. Whip until foamy.
Tear angel cake into bite-size pieces and fold all ingredients together.
To the juice, add 2 teaspoons cornstarch and cook until thickened.
Let cool and pour over cake; add red food coloring.
Use a Bundt pan and spray with Pam. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chili cheese roll
directions: Roll Velveeta cheese between waxed paper.
Whip the cream cheese.
Spread on Velveeta.
Spread chilies over cream cheese. Roll up "jelly roll" style.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: oreo cookie pudding
directions: Mix the chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Crush 10 to 12 Oreo cookies and put into bottom of bowl.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top of the cookies.
Now add 1/2 of the Cool Whip on top of the pudding mixture.
Again, crush 10 to 12 Oreo cookies and put on top of the Cool Whip layer.
Add the remaining 1/2 of the chocolate pudding mix.
Add the remaining 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Remove filling from two of the Oreo cookies.
Crush the cookies and sprinkle on top of the Cool Whip for the final touch. This looks very nice in a glass bowl.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix frozen hash browns, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, mushroom soup and 1/2 cup margarine together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan, slightly greased.
Top with cheese and sprinkle corn flakes crumbled on top.
Pour the remaining melted margarine over cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well; feeds a bunch.

title: breakfast in a glass
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and process at stir speed until well blended.

title: picnic cake
directions: Melt margarine in water.
Sift flour, salt, soda, sugar and cocoa.
Add to margarine mixture.
Beat eggs into buttermilk.
Add with vanilla.
Bake at 400° in long, flat pan about 15 minutes.

title: baked peppers, potatoes and onions
directions: Wash and clean the peppers and cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Peel the potatoes if thick-skinned, or use unpeeled new potatoes.
Cut potatoes into 1-inch chunks.
Peel the onion and cut into chunks.
Place everything in a shallow ovenproof dish and pour over the oil.
Toss the vegetables to coat them with the oil. Sprinkle with salt and lots of pepper.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for about 30 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In larger bowl, beat margarine/butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chips. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (2-inches apart) onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove cookies with spatula and let cool on wire racks. Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix all other ingredients except potato chips and butter.
Add this on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except vanilla wafers).
Mix until smooth.

title: marty's chicken-zucchini stir-fry
directions: Saute chicken chunks in non-stick skillet until nearly done. Add onions, zucchini and lemon pepper.
Stir-fry until vegetables begin to soften.
Add tomato soup (no water) and generous sprinkling of cayenne (season to taste; we like it pretty spicy). Heat to bubbling and continue to cook vegetables to your preferred tenderness.
Serve over Minute rice.

title: holiday punch
directions: In quart measure or medium bowl, stir sugar into lemon juice until dissolved.
Place ice cubes in large punch bowl.
Pour lemon juice-sugar mixture and fruit punch over ice.
Slowly add club soda or ginger ale.
Stir.
If desired, garnish with cherries and orange slices and enjoy.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: apple-nut pie* * * * *
directions: The gratin recipe must have come when we were living in Germany about the early sixties.
My reason for saying that is because it was then I first tasted kielbasa.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in medium, heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate morsels, pecans and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for one minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw the spinach and
squeeze out the water.
Add green onion, parsley and mayonnaise.
Then add salt and pepper.	Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables and crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend butter, shortening and sugar together on low speed. Sift all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Add eggs to sugar mixture, then add vanilla and mix well.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Alternate.
Pour in a tube pan; bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening in a bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in molasses and pumpkin.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and pumpkin spice together.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until a toothpick stuck in center of loaf comes out clean. Cut into thin slices and serve.

title: chicken pinwheels
directions: In small bowl, combine basil, seasoned salt and pepper and garlic powder; set aside.
Place chicken breast halves between sheets of plastic wrap and pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Lightly sprinkle seasonings over each chicken breast; top with slice of ham.
Roll up, beginning with longest side.
Place rolls, seam side down, in baking dish.
Drizzle with lemon juice; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Chill.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and margarine; beat in eggs and extract on high for 2 minutes until fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in almonds and spread into pan baking 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven until brown; remove and cool.
Cut in desired shapes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: trout almondine
directions: Wash fillets and salt and pepper.
Saute over low heat in melted 1 stick of butter and onion juice for approximately 20 to 25 minutes, depending on size of fish.
Remove fish from butter mixture to a warm platter.
Add the remaining 1/2 stick butter to skillet and saute almonds.
Add fish and lemon juice to almond mixture and cook for a few more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Put
together
the
night before.
Cube 4 slices bread. Place in a greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon
sausage
over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over
sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate. In morning, bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken souffle sandwiches
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown meat.
Add corn, water, tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Pour in a little pineapple juice and mix.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake in ungreased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check it in 1 hour with knife. It will be puffed up and golden brown on top when done.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Slice bread thin and toast.
While hot, spread immediately with butter and sprinkle generously with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon (1 teaspoon cinnamon to 1 cup sugar).

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash. Steam or boil for several minutes.
Heat butter, cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper, egg yolk, paprika and chives until these blend and make a sauce.
Pour over squash. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Coat with Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix well with confectioners sugar.
Blend in peanut butter and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pie shell and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: grandma trotter's christmas jam cake
directions: In a food chopper with a fine blade, grind together walnuts, raisins, coconut and jam; set aside.
Cream together sugar and butter and beat eggs into mixture.
