Add soda to buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 3 cups flour.

Add ground fruit and jam mixture to batter and bake in 6 very thin layers, about 1 1/4 cups batter in each, at 325° to 350° in cake pans which have been lined with greased and lightly floured waxed paper (sticking is a problem since cake is crumbly).

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend on high for about 1 minute or until well blended.
Chill before serving.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Stir or shake well before serving. Makes 4 cups.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, oleo and egg.
Add the apples and mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt to mixture and mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, blend together eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, flour, melted margarine and water. Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with the berries mixed with 1 cup sugar.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and rinse off kidney and butter beans.
Then add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nut bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Pour into
a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: peanut crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugar with a wooden spoon.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel peaches and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.

In large bowl, toss sliced peaches with flour, lemon juice, salt, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Spoon mixture into 13 x 9-inch ceramic or glass baking dish. Cover tightly with foil; bake 35 to 45 minutes until peach mixture is hot and bubbly.
About 15 minutes before peaches are cooked, separate biscuits and cut each into quarters.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugar and whipping cream in a large Pyrex measuring cup.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove; stir.
Microwave another 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave; stir real good.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Continue stirring when it begins to become stiff.
Drop on wax paper.
If it hardens, microwave for a few minutes.

title: betty's banana bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients (first 4 items).
Mix dry ingredients; add wet to dry and blend.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients into a greased loaf pan.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: rolled asparagus sandwiches
directions: Trim crust off bread.
Drain asparagus and pat dry.
Spread each slice of bread with softened butter.
Place one asparagus spear on each slice of bread and roll up.
Spread a little butter on top of each sandwich.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until slightly toasted, about 15 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter and put in baking dish.
Then combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and milk to make the dough.
Pour dough over butter. Then add boiling water, sugar and cherries.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic and salt.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Arrange in 2-quart baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, water, onion, parsley flakes and one bouillon cube.
Cook until tender and only small amount of water remains.
Put through blender; set aside.

title: triple orange molded salad
directions: Pour boiling liquid on gelatin in bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add orange sherbet; stir until melted.
Stir in 1 can mandarin segments. Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: grape salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar for dressing; refrigerate.
Combine rest of ingredients and refrigerate until serving.
Just before serving, add dressing to salad mixture and mix well.

title: pita pizza
directions: Spoon pizza sauce over one side of whole pita pockets. Sprinkle generous amounts of mushrooms, onions, bell peppers and pepperoni.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Mold into ball shapes.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix raw ground beef, seasonings, onion, cheese, rice and tomato sauce or catsup.
Use just enough sauce to mix but not soupy.
Stuff all in the 4 large green peppers. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
Remove the foil and spread catsup over and cook until peppers are starting to turn brown.

title: cream cheese raisin cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 9-inch Bundt pan. Cream butter or oleo with cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar until dissolved.
Beat in vanilla, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and blend into creamed mixture.
When batter is silky in appearance, fold in raisins. Bake in slow oven until cake tester comes out clean.
Allow cake to stand in pan 10 minutes before turning out.
This is a rich, moist pound cake that keeps well.

title: juicy chicken
directions: Bake 350° about 1 hour until brown.
May want to turn after about 40 minutes. When brown or ready to serve, boil one can of cream of chicken soup and one can water.
Pour over chicken. Serve with rice.

title: deane's hot baked fruit
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving juice.
Crush cookies.
Put fruits in buttered baking dish in layers in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with cookies.
Melt butter.
Add bourbon, brown sugar and 1/2 of reserved juice.
Pour over fruit.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no bake banana split pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted margarine; mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cornish hens in port and sour cream sauce
directions: Clean hens and remove giblets.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Slice apples and place in cavities of hens. Secure with toothpicks and rub hens with garlic.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet and brown hens on all sides.
Arrange hens in a large baking pan.
Combine chicken broth, 1 1/4 cups water and wine.
Pour over hens and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Remove hens from oven and place on platter, keeping warm.
Reserve 2 cups of pan drippings.
Saute mushrooms in 1/2 cup butter.
Add pan drippings and browning sauce.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into mushroom mixture.
Whisk in sour cream.
Do not boil!
Serve sauce with hens.

title: energy treats
directions: Mix together honey and peanut butter.
Add raisins and dry milk.
Stir in rice cereal and form into 24 small balls.
Roll in pretzel crumbs.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 24.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter; set aside. In another bowl, beat pudding as directed, then fold in Cool Whip. Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cookie crumbs, pudding mixture, cookie crumbs, pudding mixture, etc., starting and ending with cookie crumbs. Refrigerate.
If you wish, you may use flower pot lined with foil for container.
Added touches, plastic flowers and/or gummy worms.

title: phoebe's steak(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. Pour enough olive oil in a baking dish to cover the bottom.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, clove, nutmeg and allspice.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; alternate with buttermilk into which soda has been stirred; mix well.
Add by hand, blackberries with small amount of juice from berries.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Ice with 7 minute icing.

title: mamma's oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: smores
directions: In a sauce pan combine syrup and butter, bring to a boil. Remove from heat, add chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.
Add cereal and marshmallow, stir until the mixture is cooled.
Press into a greased (with butter) pan.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and brown in skillet.
Put in roaster and pour combined sauce ingredients over chicken.
Bake at 300° until chicken is soft (depends on chicken).
Second best to making it on the grill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Press
crescent
rolls down on cookie sheet and bake as directed.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Stir
honey,
oil,
eggs
and
bananas;
mix in rest of ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pans and cook at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 - 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: barbecued pork ribs(from better homes and gardens best buffets)
directions: Season meat with salt.
Place in a shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
Roast in very hot 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat. Combine remaining ingredients; brush on meat and continue baking at 350° about 30 minutes or until done, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: apricot bread
directions: Snip apricots into 4 to 5 pieces each.
Cook apricots and raisins in 2 cups water until soft and mushy, about 5 minutes.
Add sugar, spices, salt and margarine.
Mix and cool.
Add eggs, flour and soda.
Stir well with wooden spoon.
Grease, flour and wax paper line loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until done with toothpick test.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir all ingredients, except flour.
When mixed, add flour, a little at a time, to other ingredients, mixing well.
Put dough in large greased bowl; turn dough to grease the top.
Cover with foil.
Let rise at room temperature overnight, or for at least 8 hours.
Punch down dough.
Turn out onto floured board and knead. Divide into 3 parts; shape into loaves.
Put in 3 greased loaf pans; brush tops with oil.
Cover with paper towel or plastic wrap.
Let rise an additional 4 to 5 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush with butter; cool and wrap.

title: fruit punch(1921 recipe)
directions: Squeeze oranges and lemons.
Add juice to pineapple and cherries.
Put hulls in 1 quart cold water and let come to a boil. Add 4 tea bags.
Set 5 minutes.
Pour off liquid and sweeten with sugar.
When cold, add 1 quart cold water and fruit juices.
Put in refrigerator until needed.
You may use ginger ale when serving.

title: tamale dip
directions: Melt cheese and add other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and keep warm while serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken in salted water. Strip meat from bones, leaving meat in large pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Fold chicken into mixture and place in shallow casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs over the top.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: sweet and sour vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions and arrange in a 1-quart baking dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the onions.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk and bring to a boil on stove. Check to see if done by dropping a drop into cold water.
If it's hard enough to hold together, it's ready.
Remove from heat and mix in vanilla and margarine.
Beat.
Pour into greased pan and let set.

title: toasted coconut whipped cream pie
directions: Soften gelatin in
1/4	cup
cold milk.
Heat remaining milk to scalding over boiling water.
Beat egg yolks and salt; slowly add
milk,
stirring
constantly.	Return	to
double boiler; cook until	mixture coats the spoon.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.	Chill
until it begins to congeal.
Beat egg whites until stiff,
adding
sugar
gradually.
Beat
in
milk mixture and flavoring.
Fold
in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with toasted coconut.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Steam shrimp in water and keep water.
Mix cream cheese, garlic juice and onion juice with shrimp.
Add Tabasco to season. Use water you saved to thin dip.
It will get firmer after refrigerating and may need more liquid.
Refrigerate and garnish with boiled shrimp.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, mixing well. This is to pour over prepared vegetables.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over medium heat.
Coat all ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: filled chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and egg with mixer.
Stir in chocolate chips with a spoon.
Line cupcake tins with paper liner.
Put 1 tablespoon cake batter in each bottom, then 1 heaping teaspoon filling on top of cake batter, then top with another tablespoon cake batter.
Bake according to directions for 24 to 30 cupcakes on cake package.
No frosting needed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, salt and molasses.
Boil until thick and forms a hard ball in water.
Pour over corn. Stir while pouring.
Butter hands or gloves and shape into balls.

title: maple walnut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Grease foil. Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove quickly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water until tender.
Add carrots to water for 3 minutes.
Drain zucchini and carrots.
Add onions and sour cream; mix.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over stuffing; mix well.
In a large casserole dish or 13 x 9-inch pan, put a layer of stuffing down.
Use 1/2 of stuffing.
Then add vegetables.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Cover and bake until it bubbles at 350°.

title: ham or turkey roll-ups
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Wrap 1 slice of ham around 2 pieces of broccoli and 2 carrot sticks.
Heat until warm.
Heat Cheez Whiz and pour over roll-ups when ready to serve.

title: penne with vodka and tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in medium skillet.
Add onion; saute until tender, but not browned (about 5 minutes).
Stir in garlic; saute 1 minute.
At this point, add Prosciutto or panchetta and saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add vodka and red pepper; simmer 2 minutes.
Add red pepper and add tomatoes, stirring to break up tomatoes with side of spoon.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until sauce is reduced and thickened.
Slowly stir in room temperature heavy cream.
Reduce heat and cook about 3 to 5 minutes until sauce thickens.

title: cream-sicle punch
directions: Mix all together and enjoy!

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in heated pear juice. Chill until slightly set.
Mash pears with cream cheese and milk and beat well. Add jello mixture and blend well.
Mix with Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, juice of lemons and water together!

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with 1/2 onion and salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain. Mix everything in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, well beaten.
Then add the bananas, sliced thin.
Sift soda and baking powder with flour and add alternately with sour milk, then add vanilla.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately. Blend well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry mile high dessert
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, flour and nuts together.
Spread in 9x13 pan and bake 8 minutes at 325°F.
Crumble when cool and set aside.
Reserve a small amount for topping.

title: "best" beef casserole
directions: Brown beef well, adding onions.
Drain excess grease.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Season to taste.
Add soup, mixing lightly.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; reserve 1/2 cup and press the rest into a 9-inch quiche dish, bottom and sides.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and set aside.
Reduce oven to 325°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Arrange pineapple chunks in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese.
Put on top of pineapple.
Melt margarine and add Ritz crackers.
Put on top of pineapple.
Bake on 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken manicotti with chive cream sauce
directions: Cook manicotti shells in 3-quart boiling, salted water for 18 minutes or until tender but still slightly firm. Drain. Rinse with cold water then drain well. Meanwhile, for sauce, in a small, heavy saucepan stir cream cheese over medium low heat until melted. Slowly add milk, stirring until smooth. Stir in Romano or Parmesan cheese.
tags: soft style cream cheese with chives

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in oil, salt and pepper.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and roll into desired shape.
Cover with pizza makings.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add soup and milk and mix well.
Spread in casserole dish.
Cover with layer of frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place in an 8-inch single pie crust pan.
Beat eggs; mix in corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until top is brown and crisp.
Cool before serving.

title: pumpkin raisin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Into mixing bowl sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and add pumpkin mixture.
Blend just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in pecans and raisins.
Turn batter into pans and bake in preheated oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: special k cookies
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes; reduce heat.
Add the vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Add the cereal. Mix until flakes are coated. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper on a cookie sheet.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In large skillet saute cabbage and onions in Crisco until cabbage is very brown.
In separate skillet, add tomatoes to browned beef and mix.
Stir beef mixture into cabbage mixture and serve hot.

title: sweet cherry almond cake(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray a 10-inch spring-form pan with cooking oil and set aside. In a medium bowl, whisk together almonds, brown sugar and flour until well combined. In a large bowl, beat egg whites with salt until they just hold stiff peaks and fold in nut mixture gently but thoroughly. Fold in oil, vanilla and almond extract and spread batter in prepared pan. Arrange cherries evenly over batter and sprinkle with granulated sugar. Bake cake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a tester comes out clean. Cool on rack.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Mix vanilla and chopped black walnuts.
Add vanilla; chill.
Roll in small balls and pat down with a fork to size on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
When done, roll in powdered sugar.
Pack in airtight jar when cool.

title: fresh carrot cake
directions: Stir oil and sugar together; beat in eggs, one at a time.
In another bowl, sift the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add the sifted mixture to egg mixture and stir well.
(I use my mixer.)
Add the grated carrots and mix well.
Bake in a greased pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You can use loaf pans instead of the round cake pans but it will make 2 layers.
Also you can cut the ingredients in half if you don't want a large cake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries in 2 cups of water used for jello. Cranberries will explode and soften.
Dump in sugar and dry jello. Stir.
Let cool, but not jell.
Add pineapple, nuts and apples. Stir until well coated.
Pour into a large serving bowl and cover with mini marshmallows.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Prepare carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 round pans or 1 sheet pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough; otherwise, wash and dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through (use a handle of a spoon at bottom of potato so as not to cut).
Fan potatoes out after slicing.
Place potatoes in microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with butter and chopped parsley, chives and sage. Microwave at High for 10 minutes.
Rearrange after 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese. Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on High, until cheeses are melted.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add to cream mixture and beat until well blended.
Add gumdrops, coconut and oatmeal.
Blend into dough. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° or 15 to 20 minutes and cool.

title: snow salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon lemon juice; frost bowl completely. Refrigerate 24 hours, uncovered.
After serving, store covered.

title: wiener schnitzel(breaded pork cutlets)
directions: Dip cutlets into flour.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip cutlets into egg-milk mixture.
Carefully coat with bread crumbs, not too heavily.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes to seal coating.
Deep-fry cutlets until browned on both sides, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Turn cutlets several times during cooking.
Do not pierce.
Remove cutlets from lard with tongs and drain over pan for a few seconds before removing to absorbent paper.

title: riscotto pancakes
directions: Saute onion and garlic in melted butter over medium heat until tender.
Pour in broth and heat to boil.
Add rice and salt. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Parmesan and cool 20 minutes.
Add egg.
Mix well.

title: chewy goodies
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes to the mixture.
Drop on buttered waxed paper.

title: creole gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan cook onion and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly until flour is golden brown.
Stir in tomatoes, water, pepper, spices and Tabasco sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cover, simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Stir in okra and bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and crab meat, cook about 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over hot rice.
(Traditionally, rice is mounded in a heated soup plate and gumbo spooned around it.)
Serves 6.

title: paula arbuckle's corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion, garlic, broth and cumin; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add half and half, corn, chilies, cheese and Tabasco.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; brown well in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Remove chops.
Drain excess fat.
Add rice to skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place chops over top. Bring to a boil.
Simmer (covered) 45 minutes or until rice and chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: houston jail refried beans
directions: Mash beans and stir in grated cheese.
(Jack cheese is usually used, but grated American or Cheddar cheese may be used.)
Heat shortening and add bean mixture.
Stir until cheese is melted and mixture is piping hot.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Brown cooked rice, onions and diced green pepper.
Stir frequently.
Pour tomatoes over rice and other ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Add seasonings and crumbled bacon.

title: six layer taco dip
directions: Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish the jalapeno dip.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Put on top of dip.
Layer onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: orange juice-pineapple sunshine health shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Serve over ice.

title: brussels sprouts in casserole
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to directions on package.
Be sure they are tender.
Drain.
Place Brussels sprouts in greased baking dish and stir in cream of celery soup, salt and pepper. Cover with dry bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: carrot cream soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over medium heat 25 minutes or until tender.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into food processor or blender.
Blend until smooth.
Continue with balance of mixture.
Stir in white pepper; add cream and warm.
Can be served warm or chilled.

title: heavenly ham salad
directions: Prepare and cook macaroni; set aside.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, ham, celery, radishes and cucumber.
Blend together mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard and garlic salt.
Toss dressing with salad mixture.
Serve immediately or cover and chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, corn syrup, melted butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir until blended.
Stir in pecans; pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to moderate (350°) and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until firm around the edges.

title: confetti mushroom and rice side dish
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add bell pepper, onions and uncooked rice.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes, until vegetables become tender and rice begins to brown.
Add thyme, chicken broth and mushrooms; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll each into a ball and place on greased cookie sheet.
Gently flatten in a criss-cross pattern with a lightly floured fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: goulash(serves 6)
directions: Heat oil in large cast-iron skillet.
Flour meat.
Brown meat and onions together.
Lower fire and add tomatoes, salt, pepper and 3/4 can of water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add tomato sauce, potatoes, salt and pepper and more water if needed.
Cover and cook half hour.
Drain string beans and add.
Continue simmering, covered, another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Heat oleo, cocoa, water and shortening to boiling point.
Pour hot mixture over dry mixture.
Blend well. Add buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla last.
Batter will be very thin.
Bake in 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
When cake is cool, cut in half.
Take vanilla ice cream and cut in 1-inch thickness for filling for the 2 halves.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
To serve, cut in slices or squares and top with the Heavenly Hot Fudge Sauce.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes and eggs while hot with rest of ingredients. Serve while warm or refrigerate and serve later.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice until smooth.
Mix in pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Fold in cranberries and whipped cream last.
Freeze until firm.

title: pan enchiladas
directions: Heat together the enchilada sauce and tomato sauce. Add picante sauce to taste.
Layer as follows in 9 x 13-inch greased pan:

6 corn tortillas (dipped in enchilada sauce), Ranch Style beans, hamburger meat and onions, rice, 1/2 the cheese, 6 corn tortillas (dipped in enchilada sauce), remaining enchilada sauce and remaining cheese.
Cook in 425° oven until cheese melts, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, egg, banana and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: polka dot casserole
directions: Boil hamburger until done; drain.
Add all ingredients, except potatoes and cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Mix instant potatoes by the recipe on the package.
Add the potatoes, by spoonfuls on top. Break cheese into pieces and put on top of potatoes.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix flour, sugar and soda together.
Add shortening, buttermilk and dissolved yeast, mixing well with hands.
Roll out and bake at 450°.

title: miss fannie kate's slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and salt.
Pour over slaw mixture and let stand overnight.
When ready to serve drain off just the slaw you use.
The part left in the refrigerator leave in the vinegar until you use it.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups cold milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer your dish with graham crackers, then add the pudding mix.
Make as many layers as you want.
Make sure crackers are last on top and then spread chocolate icing on top.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese with sugar.
Combine cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Slice bananas over baked pie shells.
Spread mixture over bananas.
Top with blueberry filling and refrigerate.

title: beef rolls
directions: Prepare steak strips. Season with salt and pepper.

Place in the middle of each strip of steak 2 tablespoons cooked sausage, 1 dill pickle, a portion of carrots, parsley and onions. Starting at one side, roll up (like when making cabbage roll). Fasten with toothpick. Dredge each roll in the flour. Brown each roll.
Place in a casserole.
Add tomato paste to stock. Pour around beef rolls.
Cover casserole. Bake slowly at 300° or simmer for 90 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at; 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean, and let cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 10-inch square microwave (Pyrex) dish or glass pie pan.
Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Top with package of Cheddar.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for approximately 5 minutes or until Cheddar cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread cherries over bottom of square pan (8 x 8-inches). Sprinkle nuts over this, then sprinkle cake mix over it.
Sprinkle the 2 tablespoons water over top of mix.
Dot with butter slices. Bake 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: microwave caramel snappers(turtles)
directions: Arrange pecan halves in clusters of 3 on a buttered baking sheet.
Form pecans into 36 clusters.
Combine caramels, butter and milk in a glass bowl.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until caramels are melted, stirring once or twice.
Stir again until smooth.
Cool until thickened.
Spoon rounded spoonfuls onto center of each cluster.
Cool until set.
Microwave chocolate chips in glass bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until softened; stir until smooth.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Cook spaghetti in strained chicken broth; drain.
Add chili powder, salt, tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Saute onion and celery and add to spaghetti mixture. Add cut up chicken to mixture and place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrots almondine(for the grill)
directions: Combine
cornstarch,
brown
sugar,
salt,
butter
and orange juice;
cook
until
thickened.
Arrange
carrots	and almonds in a large double thickness square of heavy duty foil. Pour sauce over
carrots
and	almonds;
seal	foil securely. Cook on gas grill at medium heat setting for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: scrumptious apricot stuffing
directions: Chop onion, celery and garlic.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until onion is clear in color and celery is tender.
Be careful not to burn garlic.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Add water and baby food.
Mix until moist.
Add more water, if necessary.
Stuff bird and cook as directed.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add bouillon cubes, then boiling water. Cover and bring to boil.
Then simmer gently until done.
This soup is superb.
Stores well and freezes well in tightly covered containers.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad 2
directions: May use 1/2 to 3/4 cup Marzetti Slaw Dressing for sauce in place of mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and garlic salt.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Make a sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened and smooth; remove from fire.
Add onions and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add beaten egg yolks and blend well.
Carefully add the asparagus, cut in small pieces. Season to taste.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: baked apple butter
directions: Cook apples, quartered but not peeled, in 1/2 cup water until soft.
Run through colander.
Use this applesauce, 6 cups cider, brown sugar and spices; put in large pan and bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours, stirring thoroughly every 1/2 hour.

title: jim bennett's spaghetti
directions: In a saucepan, mix Lawry's sauce mix, tomatoes, olives and salad oil. Mix thoroughly.
Bring to boil. Then reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often.
Brown the meat while stirring in all of the seasonings, onion and bell pepper.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add the drained noodles and sauce to the meat mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: corned beef and cabbage dinner
directions: Place brisket in large pot, covering completely with water. Bring to a boil and then let simmer for 2 hours.
Add onions, carrots, potatoes and cabbage.
Cook 1 more hour.
Carve meat against the grain. Delicious 1 pot meal.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Mix oranges, cottage cheese and dry jello. Add nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar. Let stand. Beat eggs slightly. Stir in oil and vanilla. Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir into apple-sugar mixture. Stir in walnuts. Pour into greased and floured oblong pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla pudding.
Add flavorings and half and half; beat.
Add pecans.
Fold in whipping cream.
Freeze.
(I freeze about 5 hours before serving and place container in my freezer so mixture will be a little stiffer.) Makes about 1 gallon.

title: chocolate cream cheese icing
directions: Combine Crisco and softened cream cheese.
Mix powdered sugar and cocoa. Add with cream and vanilla until spreading consistency. Spread on cooled cake.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Cook and peel yams and cut in quarters.
Place yams in a 13 x 9 greased pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients; stir constantly.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over yams and bake for 15 more minutes.
Baste often with the juice. Serve hot.

title: applesauce cake (no egg)
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add raisins.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Dissolve baking soda in warm water; add applesauce.
Stir immediately into sugar, shortening and raisin mixture.
Add dry sifted ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 10-inch pan in 375° oven for 3/4 hour.

title: daisy's sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes.
Boil
until soft.
Drain off water.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain excess grease.
In a large baking dish, pour potatoes, ground beef mixture, cream of mushroom soup and evaporated milk.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Add 3 tablespoons melted butter. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix the sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 25 medium size pies.

title: macadamia brownies
directions: Cream the flour, sugar and margarine together well.
Add eggs and cocoa.
Cream with flour mixture and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine broth, celery and onion.
Cook 20 minutes covered. Add potatoes and vegetables.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add soup and cheese cut into small cubes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and marinate awhile.
It may not take the full bag of Fritos.
Add these just before serving.

title: bailey's cheesecake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In spring-form pan, mix graham cracker crumbs, packed brown sugar and butter.
Pat mixture into the bottom of the pan (for crust).
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until puffy.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and blend one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven and turn to 275°.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Turn oven to 300° last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream.
Cook until mixture is thick and brown.
Remove from heat.
Combine milk, flour and egg yolks. Stir in first mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place peeled and deveined shrimp in single layer on bottom of broiling pan.
Crush 4 garlic cloves with garlic press or slice very thinly.
Add butter, lemon juice, salt and oregano.
Heat until shrimp are pink.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Beat in eggs and slowly stir in milk and vanilla.
Stir in bread cubes, raisins and butter.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife stuck near center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.
About 1 cup each.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Blend well and spoon into oven proof dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: bacon egg and cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients adding as much mayonnaise as you like and stir until well mixed.
Makes enough filling for 11 full sandwiches or 30 cocktail sandwiches.

title: chicken puff pie(serves 4)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except crescent rolls and parsley flakes.
Cook until heated thoroughly.

title: fairy cake
directions: Beat 5 egg yolks 5 minutes. Add the cold water and beat 5 minutes more.
Add the granulated sugar and beat 5 minutes more. Add the cake flour (sifted 3 times), salt and vanilla. Beat 5 egg whites until frothy. Add cream of tartar.
Beat stiff, about 15 minutes.
Fold into first mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.
Cool and ice.

title: cinnamon nut toast
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons margarine on each slice of toast.
Sprinkle about 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar mixture on each.
Broil until bubbly.
Cut in triangles. Serve warm.

title: seven layer supper
directions: Layer
ingredients
in order given in a casserole dish. Sprinkle
with
salt
and
pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° about an hour until vegetables are tender.

title: mac's special stuffing
directions: This recipe is dedicated to my late husband Mac.
He always enjoyed cooking and often tried new things by mixing a "schoosh" of this and a pinch of that.
This recipe is a document of what he did often "on the fly".
I hope you enjoy it!

title: pea and bean salad
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar, vinegar and oil, add the rest of ingredients, stir well and let stand overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and form into desired shape. Punch holes
in
top and add catsup.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: almond green beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and soy sauce.
Layer half each of the beans, mushrooms, bean sprouts and soup mixture in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Place undrained sweet potatoes in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until heated through; drain.
Combine with next 5 ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 of the eggs and 1/2 cup pizza sauce. Stir in 1/2 cup crumbs, onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Pat 1/3 of the meat into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain mushrooms.
Combine with remaining egg and 1/2 cup crumbs, cheese, parsley and oregano.
Spread evenly over meat in pan. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Heat remaining pizza sauce and pour over meat loaf and serve.

title: "special treat"
directions: Have a platter ready to lay and separate crackers.
They cook fast.
Do not stack crackers.
Moderately heat oil or margarine. Lightly brown (golden brown) each cracker.
Do not overcook.
Take up crackers and roll each cracker in sugar.
Be sure to cover both sides.
Store crackers in airtight container after they have cooled.
Great for special occasions.

title: easy avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add water to beet juice to equal 2 cups.
Bring liquid to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in jello until dissolved.
Add cold water, onion, horseradish, salt and vinegar.
Chill until partially set.
Add beets, celery and olives.
Pour into 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrot, raisins, coconut and pecans.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter. Add mushrooms.
Combine soup with sour cream, milk and seasonings in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add ham and noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese and overlap tomato slices on top.
Toss croutons in 2 tablespoons melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt in microwave chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter. Stir well and mix with Crispix cereal until well coated.
Put powdered sugar into paper sack; add coated cereal.
Shake until well coated.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers.
Mix with pecans, milk, cherries and 1/2 bag of coconut.
Put other half of coconut on waxed paper. Pour mixture on waxed paper and roll, then put in refrigerator and chill.
Slice off and serve anytime.
Great for parties and Christmas.

title: microwave cranberry sauce
directions: In a deep, 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine cranberries, apple, raisins, apple juice, cinnamon and lemon peel.
Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes, or until skins on cranberries pop, stirring once.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: karen's crispy onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Soak in ice water for about 2 hours.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Whisk in water all at once until batter is smooth.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before using.

title: ethel's peanut butter pie
directions: Cut peanut butter into powdered sugar until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs into baked pie crust.
Prepare custard with milk.
Pour into shell.
Chill.
Beat cream until stiff.
Spread onto pie.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.

title: kookie cookies
directions: Spread corn chips in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie crust; cover with second crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate and use for veggie dip.

title: peach-caramel cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Cut up peaches and set aside.
Crumble sugar-nut mixture from refrigerated caramel rolls in saucepan; add flour, lemon peel and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in ginger ale and reserved syrup; mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened; stir in butter.
Add peaches; bring to boiling.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Immediately separate caramel rolls; arrange atop the hot mixture.
Bake at 400° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt three times.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour to sugar-butter-egg mixture.
Add vanilla. Bake in 3 or 4 layers in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: western antipasto salad
directions: Combine salad oil, vinegar, garlic and seasonings ahead of time to allow flavors to blend.
Break lettuce into small pieces; add remaining ingredients.
Just before serving, add salad dressing.

title: chicken italian in foil
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise onto an 18 x 12-inch double layer of foil.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add peppers and tomatoes.
Lay chicken on top of vegetables and brush with oil.
Mix catsup, oregano and butter.
Pour over chicken.
Wrap foil securely around chicken and vegetables.
Bake until tender for one hour or grill 5 inches from coals for 25 to 30 minutes on each side.
Oven temperature 400°; bake 1 hour.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cover chicken in water for boiling; add bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Allow to cool; discard skin, veins and bones.
Dice meat to bite size pieces.
Saute onion, bell pepper and pimento in butter.
Add soup, milk and chicken.
When heated, add the beaten egg yolks, cooking slowly until thick (in double boiler).
Just before serving, add sherry.
This should be thick enough without adding flour.
Six times this recipe will serve 50.
Serve from chafing dish in patty shells or on toast.
Wonderful holiday fare!

title: snacks that kids can make
directions: Mix ingredients;
roll into snakes or other shapes on powdered milk board.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions. Chop beef in a blender.
Mix with cheese (room temperature). Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce. Roll into ball. Sprinkle with paprika. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until needed.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and mix well.
Pour into a buttered pie plate.
A 9 1/2-inch fruit pie plate works well. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Put liquids in largest bowl.
Then add other ingredients. Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
This is great with taco or picante sauce.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook broccoli as directed, rice also.
Mix together.
Add soups, straight from cans, and Cheez Whiz.
Blend well.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Chop dates; add boiling water and let cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; mix well.
Add orange rind and juice to date and water mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Blend date mixture into creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Beat egg whites and fold into cake batter.
Pour into floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken in lemon and garlic
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and rub with garlic. Combine ginger, mustard, thyme, poultry seasoning and salt. Sprinkle over chicken.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter.
Add 1/2 of the sugar.
Beat the eggs very light; add the remainder of the sugar.
Combine the 2 mixtures; add the milk.
Stir together the baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg with the flour and add to the mixture with enough more flour to handle, having the dough as soft as possible.
Toss on a floured board and knead lightly.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with a doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot fat; drain on brown paper.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients slowly, adding horseradish and sour cream to taste.
Heat in saucepan until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: editor's choice pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until they are light and fluffy.
Add pineapple and juice, flour, sugars and baking soda. Mix these ingredients well by hand (if you use an electric mixer, too much air is beaten in).
Then stir in walnuts and spread the contents of the bowl evenly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 or 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
After the cake cools, cover it with Cream Cheese Ginger Frosting, then sprinkle some additional walnuts on top.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: antipasto
directions: Drain and rinse vegetables, olives and artichoke hearts. Drain water/oil from tuna.
Combine with seafood sauce and chill overnight.
Nice to add also are mushrooms and pickled peppers. Serve as a first coarse with crusty bread.

title: reuben fondue
directions: Drain sauerkraut thoroughly and chop.
Mix cream cheese, onion, corned beef, sauerkraut and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Dip each ball into flour, then cream; roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil (about 2-inches deep) in fondue pot and cook balls until golden brown.

title: green jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool.
Stir in Pet milk. In another bowl, mix pineapple, lemon juice, cottage cheese, nuts, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix together with jello and chill.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Gently pull off cabbage leaves.
Simmer in 1-inch boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and lay out, ready for filling. Combine meat with egg, onion, rice and seasonings.
Fill leaves loosely with mixture.
Roll up each, folding leaves under.
Place in a greased skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Drain tomatoes, place on edge.
Pour in 1 cup liquid.
Cook on high until steam appears.
Turn to simmer for 1 hour.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine 1st 9 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually stir 1/4 cup milk into flour, making a smooth paste. Stir into soup.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups milk. Cook over medium heat until soup is thickened.
Makes 9 cups.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Form into a loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes, uncovered.
Drain off grease.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a large bowl, layer the ingredients.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup of coconut and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy vegetable spread
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Mix together cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir in vegetables and pepper.
Chill.

title: fried canada goose and arkansas rice
directions: Salt, pepper and (optional) sprinkle pieces with pepper duck, a waterfowl seasoning available at some gourmet outlets.
Dredge in flour.
Brown goose pieces on both sides.
Add 1 cup of water and bring to a simmer.
Cook 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Serve on Arkansas Cooked Rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chow mein noodles. Refrigerate several hours.
Add noodles just before serving.
Put on bed of lettuce.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill overnight.
Using whole pumpernickel or rye bread, cut out top and inside.
Fill will Dill Dip.
Place bread that was cut out of loaf around loaf for dipping.

title: mama's caramel nut icing
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball stage (about 5 minutes). Cool and beat before adding nuts.
Use your favorite layer cake recipe.
Makes enough icing for 4 layers.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs, chocolate chips and sour cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Fold in chocolate chips and sour cream.
Pour into lightly greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour in a preheated
350° oven, then cool 45 minutes before
removing from pan.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, evaporated and condensed milk.
Add a little milk.
Pour into freezer cannister and add milk to fill line.

title: tuna boat
directions: Drain tuna then mix tuna with mayonnaise.
Cut the green peppers lengthwise in half and remove insides.
Fill halves with tuna mixture and lay 1 slice of cheese over each pepper.
Can be served cold or hot.
Put in microwave for 1 or 2 minutes.

title: refrigerator cucumber slices
directions: In a large container combine cucumbers and onions.
In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers, mix well.

title: aunt mamie mullen's pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs; add Karo syrup, sugar, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
Mix until well blended.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking until knife blade inserted comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: autumn festival fluff
directions: Make one day ahead.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Press 2/3 of crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve remaining crumbs.
Beat cream cheese and white sugar; fold into whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of cream cheese mixture over crust in pan.
Add apple filling and sprinkle with cinnamon (if desired).
Combine powdered sugar and 1/3 cup peanut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture over apples.
Top with remaining whipped topping mixture and then remaining graham cracker crumbs.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
A little lengthy, but very good.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 3 tablespoons
sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and 2 cups sugar.
Mix oil, orange juice, vanilla and eggs.
Add together.
Put a layer of batter in pan, then layer of apple mixture.
Put batter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pan roasted garlic chicken
directions: With a cleaver or sharp knife cut each chicken breast into 4 pieces.
Put aside.
Slice garlic.
In large pot or Dutch oven heat olive oil.
Brown garlic in oil.
Add chicken and brown well on both sides.
Add 1 cup of the water and reduce heat to low-medium. Pot roast chicken for about 1 1/2 hours, until fork-tender.
(Add mushrooms for the last 15 minutes.)
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with pan drippings over pasta or rice.

title: punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Cook 3 minutes to make syrup.
Let cool, then add juices.
Mash and add bananas.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 3 to 4 hours ahead and add Seven-Up.
I use clean plastic milk gallon containers to freeze this in.

title: escarole medley
directions: Wash escarole very good; cut up and add salt.
Boil until tender; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, brown garlic in olive oil.
Don't burn it.
Add mushrooms and black olives.
Cook a few minutes.
Add escarole; cook about 5 minutes longer.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with white rice or meat.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Cook on stove on medium heat to dissolve sugar. Add pecans. Cook, stirring constantly, until pecans are thoroughly sugared and no liquid is left in pot. Spread on wax paper and cool. Store in airtight container.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomatoes, corn and cheese casserole
directions: Put a layer of corn in a buttered baking dish, layer of tomatoes, layer of cheese and repeat.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Dot with butter and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: swiss cherry cheese torte
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, using 2 (8-inch) pans. Cool and split each layer in half, making 4 layers.
Cream together cream cheese (softened) and lemon juice.
Add to this the canned frosting.
Mix well.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken breasts on both sides in skillet.
Add rice and cook as directed on box.
During last few minutes of cooking, put pieces of cheese on top of chicken.
When cheese is melted, this dish is done.

title: aunt sharon's cream biscuits
directions: In bowl, place flour.
Add the cream.
With fork stir until soft. On floured surface, knead lightly 5 times.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter or glass dipped in flour. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Layer in glasses; alternate cream mix with fruit.
End with fruit on top.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 5.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate until cold. Serve with crackers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together Marshmallow Fluff and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Use any fruit in season (grapes, apples, pears, bananas, etc.).

title: lemon velvet jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello mix in 1 cup hot water and cool.
Put cake mix in large bowl and add oil.
Beat, adding one egg at a time. Lastly, add jello.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Glaze while hot with 2 cups powdered sugar mixed with 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Punch small holes in cake with ice pick and pour icing over hot cake.

title: applesauce raisin
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, raisins, nutmeg, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside in another bowl.
Beat eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Pour over flour mixture until moistened. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in bars.

title: ninety-minute rolls
directions: Combine 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast. Heat milk, water and margarine until liquids are 120° to 130°. Add dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; grease top and cover.
Place bowl in warm place to rise until doubled.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter in angel food pan.
Slice apples (paper thin).
Sprinkle cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts. Pour rest of batter over cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream grated cheese and margarine; mix salt, pepper and flour. Add to cheese mixture and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix. Roll in walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork (about 1/4 inch thick).
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a serving dish.

title: chicken francesa
directions: Remove tenderloin from each chicken and save. Fillet each half of chicken breast into 2 slices to yield 12 pieces.
Use flat of meat pounder and pound each piece including tenderloins.
Soak all chicken in milk for about 10 minutes.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley.
Dredge each piece of chicken through bread crumb mixture, making sure each slice is well coated.
Pour olive oil into a large skillet and quickly braise breasts on each side until lightly browned.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon of oil from skillet, leaving residue from chicken.
Add white wine and boil until liquid is reduced by half. Add chicken broth and lemon juice. Boil again until liquid is reduced by half.
Pour over chicken, then drizzle Grand Marnier over each slice. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until liquid begins to bubble. Serve with buttered noodles and green vegetable.

title: wedding soup
directions: Wash chicken and place in a large pot.
Add water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Skim well and add celery, parsley, carrots and onion.
Cover and simmer for about 3 hours or until chicken is tender and meat starts to fall from bones.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Blend in zucchini and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour for large loaves or for 40 to 45 minutes for mini-loaves.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 large loaves or 6 mini-loaves.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Place rice in bottom of ovenproof dish.
Add soup, butter and mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for approximately 50 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and put in refrigerator. When firm, roll into balls and return to refrigerator.
Combine in double boiler chocolate chips and shortening.
When melted, dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Slice the quart of berries and pat dry with a paper towel. Spread berries in the baked and cooled shell.
Combine water, cornstarch and sugar in a pan.
Cook to boil and boil for 2 minutes until mixture is clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
While still hot, pour evenly over berries.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream or topping.

title: ruth lyons' coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together sugar, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Add the oil and stir until crumbly. Reserve and set aside 3/4 cup of the mixture for topping. Add vinegar to the milk and stir into the sugar mixture. Add the egg and soda and mix well. Pour into 13x9 pan. Sprinkle with the reserved topping. Bake 30 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook onions, celery, butter and bouillon until celery is soft and tender.
May need to add a little more water but don't cook too fast as the water boils away.
Add all of this to the bread crumb mixture and toss lightly.
May also add juice from your turkey.
I like really moist.
Bake in casserole dish at 350°.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure water in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast; add milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; let rise 1/2 hour.
Punch down; shape in rolls.
Let rise 1/2 hour. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Melt cheese and margarine together.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat until warm.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In a bowl stir together first four ingredients until blended. Stir in chicken, celery, water chestnuts and onion.
Add macaroni.
Toss to coat well.
Spoon int 2 quart casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until done.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together in microwave or on stove.
In mixer, beat eggs, flour and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate mixture and blend well. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: excellent way to fix ham
directions: Mix last three ingredients; brush over ham and wrap in foil and bake.
Bake about 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 350° oven.

title: moms favorite company's coming salad
directions: In a large bowl mix together by hand the fruit cocktail, oranges and pineapple with juice.
Add pudding mixes and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture and mix.
(Might need more flour.)
Chill at least 2 hours.
Roll and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki veggies
directions: Melt
butter in saucepan; add teriyaki	sauce
and
then spices.
Bring to quick boil, then pour
evenly
over
veggies. Cook 5 to 10 minutes on high before serving.
(Depends
on	how crisp you like vegetables.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onion in butter with bay leaf until the onion is clear.
Add chopped green pepper, chopped broccoli, water or broth and salt.
Cook 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender, but still bright green.
Puree with milk in blender until smooth.
Whisk in sour cream and seasonings.
Steam broccoli just until done. Combine flowerets with soup in a large double boiler.
Heat gently and serve.
Top with minced scallions.

title: my friend's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna, adding a little cooking oil to water to prevent noodles from sticking; drain.
Cook ground beef, onion and garlic together over medium flame until brown.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook over low flame until somewhat thickened, about 10 minutes.

title: wild rice soup with bacon
directions: Fry bacon; drain and reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute rice, onion, carrots and celery in bacon fat for 5 minutes.
Return bacon to kettle, stir in 4 cups stock.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, stir constantly until rice is tender, about 40 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup of cream.
Mix the butter and flour; whisk in soup, cook, stirring constantly until the soup thickens and bubbles, about 1 minute.
Stir in part or all of the remaining 1/2 cup stock and 1/2 cup cream, if a thinner soup is desired.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together and beat well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and Crisco over hot water and spread on top.
Cut into pieces before chocolate sets completely.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Sift and add the flour, cocoa, salt and soda. Add milk and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 7 minutes. When cooled, fill with filling.

title: ranch mash potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Mash potatoes with milk and sour cream; add Ranch dressing.
Blend well.
Add cheese and bacon.
Serve.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Mix all, except 1/2 of noodles.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in very large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix together the buttermilk, eggs and Wesson oil; add to dry ingredients.
Place entire mixture in airtight container and refrigerate; use as needed.
(This batter will keep 4 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.)
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, onion and eggs; add to broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Pour margarine over and spread stuffing mix top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat tortillas in oven.
I use foil and put melted butter between each one, stacked and seal.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or so.
Saute in the oil the cabbage, carrot, onions and garlic. Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, 2 teaspoon chili powder or more to your own taste, 1 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Add 1 cup cut up chicken pieces and 1 can refried beans.
Simmer gently until heated thoroughly.
Scoop hot filling into tortilla; add chopped ingredients.
Enjoy!

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Heat fat in skillet and brown chicken in it.
Place browned chicken, onion, celery and green beans in a casserole.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake at 350° until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk on low speed until combined.
Beat for 2 minutes on high.
Pour into pie crust. Chill for 20 minutes or until filling is thickened.
Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle peanut butter cups on top.
Chill.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Boil chicken until tender and chop coarsely and set aside. Put the next 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven and simmer until onions are clear and tender.
Add chopped chicken and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce last.
More can be added when reheating if desired.
Just like pork barbecue!!

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine yeast, water and sugar.
Set aside.
Combine flour, dry milk and salt.
By the time you have done this, the yeast mixture should be bubbly.
Add oil to yeast mixture, then add liquid to dry ingredients and butter flavor.
If you have dough hooks, mix until bread is no longer sticky.
If you don't have the hooks, mix until dry ingredients are incorporated.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead until no longer sticky.
Put dough in a warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down.
Make into rolls or bread. This makes rolls, bread, cinnamon rolls, cinnamon bread, etc.

title: thanksgiving onion pie
directions: Slice onions and saute in butter. Toast bread and butter, if desired.
Cut toast into 1-inch cubes.
Layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole pan. Spread onions on top of bread cubes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over onions.
Beat eggs.
Add pepper and milk. Pour this mixture over top of ingredients.
Cover and chill 6 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: apple walnut crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spoon apple pie filling evenly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Grate rind from lemon; sprinkle over filling.
Cut lemon in half.
Juice lemon halves. Drizzle juice over filling.
Sprinkle with half the cinnamon; pour dry cake mix evenly over apples so it reaches all sides of pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon over cake mix.
Sprinkle walnuts over top; drizzle melted butter over entire pan.
Bake in 350° oven until top is golden and bubbly and walnuts have browned about 55 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and let cool for 10 minutes. To serve, spoon crisp into bowls; top with scoop of vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: tomato and rice soup
directions: Brown beef in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add water, tomatoes, pepper and salt.
Bring to a brisk boil.
Add rice and allow to boil a second time.
Cover and reduce heat 40 minutes.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Brown in vegetable oil.
Add onions.
Blend soup, sherry, juice from mushrooms and garlic salt. Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender (or can cover and bake at 350°).
Serve over hot rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add flour and stir for about 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in warm milk.
Turn up heat and continue stirring until sauce is just at the boiling point.
Turn down and simmer until sauce thickens.
Add pepper and hot sauce.
Stir in heavy cream and simmer briefly.
Stir in 3/4 of the shredded cheese and stir until melted.
Combine cheese sauce and cooked macaroni.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: grateful mary
directions: Put tomato juice, yogurt, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce in your blender.
Blend on medium speed for about 2 minutes, until smooth.
Pour into 4 tall glasses over ice. Place a celery stick in each glass for garnish.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs in a large bowl.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in peanut butter chips and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix ingredients until real soupy and cook 1 hour at 350°. Makes a delicious dressing that really does not need giblet gravy.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, gently combine potatoes and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and onion.
Stir into potato mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a preheated greased skillet.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve with syrup, if desired.
Yield:
12 (2-inch) pancakes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef; add taco seasoning and 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.

Let simmer 10 minutes. Form pie crust with crescent rolls; put thin layer of corn chips on top of crust. Pour in beef; top with sour cream. Add 6 slices American cheese. Add another layer of corn chips and spot with butter. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Drain peaches and chop.
Combine with the well drained pineapple and remaining ingredients except nuts.
Pile lightly into the crumb crust and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in small mixing bowl as given in order.
This is good served with cauliflower, broccoli, celery and carrot sticks or potato chips.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and egg in bowl. Beat until light. Gradually blend in combined flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Stir in vanilla and apples. Turn mixture into an ungreased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Serve warm or cold topped with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rhubarb, sugar, eggs, flour and milk.
Pour on crust and bake at 350° until rhubarb is tender, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool. Put topping on top, if desired.

title: 5 minute chocolate chip cookie bar
directions: Mix flour, margarine, brown sugar and vanilla together with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Toss in chips and nuts.
Mix a bit. (If necessary to moisten, add 1/4 cup water).
Press into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown at the edges.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding some of the chicken broth, if needed, to keep it from being too dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Place all ingredients in 3-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not underbake.
Better if made a day before and kept in refrigerator overnight, then baked and served hot.

title: pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press cream cheese in bottom of a 9-inch glass pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese and layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins until tender (5 minutes).
Drain raisins.
Pour them into an unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg well; add melted butter, sugar, flour, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour over raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: jiffy tuna dinner
directions: Grease 1-quart baking dish.
Mix all together except potato chips.
Put a layer of crushed chips on bottom, then layer with mixture and sprinkle chips on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly hot.
Serves 4.

title: 2, 2 and 2 ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth and add enough milk to make 1 gallon.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until hard.
Let stand approximately 15 minutes and serve.
Makes a smooth, creamy ice cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a buttered casserole dish. Mix 1 cup light brown sugar, 1/3 cup plain flour, 1 cup finely chopped pecans and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix according to package directions.
Cool.

title: magic cookie recipe
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add top layer of graham cracker crumbs. Pat evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients into crumb mixture.
Spread evenly with spoon.
Pour can of sweetened condensed milk.
Mix evenly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool--cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: magic squares
directions: Melt margarine or butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make crust out of crushed graham crackers.
Put milk over graham cracker crust. Layer with coconut and top with M&M's.
Cook approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemonade, milk, and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour pineapple over top.
Sprinkle box of dry cake mix over top.
Then pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Bake about 35 minutes.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Beat oleo, then add sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually. Bake on ungreased pans at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in quart jars.
