Boil together the vinegar, sugar, salt and ground mustard.
Make sure this mixture is boiling good, then pour over pickles.
Seal while hot.

title: praline cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; set aside.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, bread crumbs, egg and cheese.
Form into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in skillet until cooked through.

title: old-fashioned coconut cake
directions: Heat milk and butter in saucepan until butter is melted.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla, then flour, mixing well after each addition.
Pour in milk and butter mixture, then mix well.
Pour batter in three 9-inch greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat to cool.
Blend bananas in a blender with lemon juice.
Add to remaining juices.
Add water/sugar mixture and put in a container to freeze.
Thaw to a slushy stage and add 2 quarts of 7-Up.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and pour in tube pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: beefburger specials
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into patties.
Grill 4-inches from coals about 7 minutes on each side.
Serve on toasted bun with slice of sweet Vidalia onion.

title: shake-a-sack cracker snack
directions: In a large plastic
bag
combine
the
cheese crackers, oyster crackers, pretzel nuggets,	salad dressing mix and dill weed. Close the top of the
bag and shake until everything is mixed together well.

title: scotcheroos
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook sugar and light syrup over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in the Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let harden.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels over hot water (but not boiling water).
Stir to blend and spread over cereal mixture.
Chill about 5 minutes until top is firm.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: george delight
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: peg's famous ice cream torte
directions: Combine cake mix, pecans, butter and sugar in large bowl.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Turn into unbuttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 12 minutes. Remove from pan and mix with a fork until crumbly.
Cool completely.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Press 1/3 of crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with 1/2 the ice cream.
Repeat, ending with the last 1/3 of crumbs.
Freeze overnight.
Makes 15 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples.
Chop and measure 1 3/4 cups into a large bowl.
Add sugar and let stand 10 minutes.

title: bear dijonnaise
directions: Trim all fat off bear meat.
Be sure to clean out kernel (musk gland) to avoid gamy taste.
Cut meat into 3-inch cubes. Season flour with Parmesan and black pepper.
Mix well.
Roll meat cubes into seasoned flour.
Cover well.

title: greek pasta salad with shrimp
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add linguine and shrimp.
Toss to blend.

title: gail's sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine butter and chicken.
Sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: muffins
directions: Place flour,
sugar,
baking powder and salt in a bowl. Add egg, milk and oil to bowl and stir until batter is smooth. Fill cupcake
papers
about
full
of
batter and bake 25 minutes in a covered Dutch oven.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix all together in greased 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake next day, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes, then uncovered, at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: linguine with vegetables
directions: Saute the first 6 items together for about 5 minutes.
Add the pea pods, optional cashews and wine; cook another 2 minutes or so. Toss with linguine and Parmesan cheese.

title: share brandied fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients in a clean, nonmetal bowl; stir gently.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 3 weeks, stirring fruit twice a week.
Serve fruit over ice cream or pound cake, reserving at least 1 cup starter at all times.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Add this topping on top before baking.

title: "garbage"
directions: Melt over double boiler the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour melted mixture over Rice Chex, raisins and peanuts.
Put into garbage bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated and put into refrigerator until cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and cook until browned. Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 3 pounds of meat.

title: oven stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until well done; slice off top.
Scoop out.
Add to all the ingredients, mixed.
Beat with mixer until mashed potato texture.
Scoop back into empty potato shell (overstuffed). Sprinkle with paprika.
Reheat 20 to 40 minutes at 375° (20 if done immediately, 40 if refrigerated).

title: pork adobo
directions: Soak pork in the ingredients for 2 hours or overnight.
Cook until tender.
Serve hot with rice and vegetables.

title: marshmallow cereal bars(microwavable)
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place butter and marshmallows in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave uncovered on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Add cereal.
Press mixture in pan using buttered back of spoon.
Cool.
Makes 16 or 24 bars.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Stir after 20 minutes.
Stir again after 20 minutes.
Bake until done.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add pasta and mix .
Cover bowl and chill in refrigerator.
More mayonnaise may be added if salad sets overnight.

title: chicken wing appetizers
directions: Wash chicken wings, breaking in two at the joints.
Remove tips and keep for soup.
Combine the crumbs and all the dry ingredients.
Dip wing pieces in melted butter and then into the crumb mixture.
Place wings in a single layer on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake uncovered for 18 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut rolls; spread on both sides with margarine mixture.
Add layer of ham and cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 72 rolls.
Freezes well.

title: poke casserole
directions: Cook
rice
in
water
according to package directions. Drain poke.
Saute
onion
in butter.
Add all ingredients in baking dish.
Save
a little of the Cheez Whiz and put on top. Bake until bubbly in oven at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream and 1/4 teaspoon of oregano.
Form into small balls; cook in skillet, turning to brown evenly.
Remove to serving dish.
Make gravy by adding water to skillet, scraping bits of browned meat from bottom of pan.
Add sour cream and oregano.
Heat until mixture is hot; pour over meatballs.

title: ghoul-ade(black punch for halloween party)
directions: Mix everything, except ginger ale together in a large glass or plastic bowl or pitcher.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale. Serve over ice.
"It's black as midnight and frightfully delicious!"

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water together. Add pie filling and pineapple; refrigerate overnight. Next day, mix together topping.

title: marbled peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in heavy 4-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla until well blended.
Divide mixture into equal portions. Stir chocolate chips into 1 portion until melted and blended. Stir peanut butter into second portion until blended.
Pour peanut butter mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with chocolate mixture.
Cut through fudge with knife several times for marble effect.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Makes 5 1/2 pounds.

title: quick & easy breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and place pieces in greased baking dish (13x9x2). Brown and drain sausage in skillet.
Spoon browned sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt, and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35-40 min.
(The cheese will rise to the top during baking.)

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugars and cream again.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and alternate with milk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until shrimp are cooked through, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Chill until syrupy (not congealed).
Whip milk and add jello.
Stir in sugar, pineapple and pecans.
Line bottom of dish with graham or vanilla crumbs, mixed with butter.
Pour in above jello mixture.
Spread crumb mixture over top.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve. Makes 16 servings.
Whipping cream may be substituted for milk.

title: *graham wafer toffees
directions: Place 12 double graham crackers on a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet.
Boil the brown sugar and margarine for 2 minutes.
Pour this over the crackers.
Sprinkle the nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes before cutting into squares and bars.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put
all
ingredients in Pyrex dish;
stir
and
cover. Begin cooking at 350°, then turn oven down
to
and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: baked ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix together onion, Worcestershire, mustard, mayonnaise and poppy seed.
Spread on one side of bun.
Make up the sandwiches and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time and put in refrigerator.

title: bibingka(rice cake from the pilipino ethnic culture)
directions: *Mochiko can be purchased at Hughes markets, any Asian store.

title: spanish rice with sausage
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, covered.

title: merry-go-round cake
directions: Put the animal crackers on a piece of wax paper.
Decorate the crackers with tubes of icing. Take your time. When they are done, bake your favorite 2 layer cake. Put your favorite icing on it.

title: fruity tootie smoothie(or you name it, it is in this smoothie)
directions: Add the ice cream and yogurt and Equal to the pop and ice. Then whatever you would like: strawberries, bananas, peaches, plums. Mix on high in a blender or smoothie machine until nice and smooth. If not getting smooth, add another can of pop. Pour into glass and drink with a straw.

title: maple pecan cream pie
directions: In 2-quart glass measure with handle, stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk, pure maple syrup, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Microwave on 100% power (High) 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes, then after each minute until thickened and bubbly.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly about 1 1/2 hours. Stir in pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: slumgullion spread
directions: Mix all together with 1 cup of mayonnaise.
Very good on crackers.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces and brown.
Drain grease and set aside.
In skillet, melt oleo and saute onions, bell pepper and celery until limp.
To this add Accent, sugar, pepper, parsley, salt, Tabasco sauce and garlic powder.
Simmer a few minutes, then add pimento and sausage.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice.

title: frozen bing cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Cut into individual servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Gradually add to milk. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Add small amount to egg yolks. Stir into remaining mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add butter. Pour into baked pie shell. Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chips and peanut butter in microwave.
Pour over Chex mix.
Put in grocery bag with 1 to 2 cups confectioners sugar.
Shake well.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and seasoning.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese, heat until cheese melts.

title: fried potato wedges
directions: Half unpeeled potatoes, then cut each half lengthwise into 3 or 4 wedges.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add potato wedges, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes or until fork-tender and golden brown.

title: pumpkin log
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat eggs for 5 minutes, until light and creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into jelly roll pan (with waxed paper on) and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Immediately turn out onto linen towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll cake with the towel and place on wire rack to cool.
After completely cool, spread with filling. Roll it again.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Drain off 1/2 of each can of tomatoes and put in casserole dish and stir in bread crumbs, basil, garlic powder, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Mix together.
Put in oven to warm 375° (about 15 minutes).
Mix together the cheese and more bread crumbs.
Put on top and dot with olive oil.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: heavenly cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan well with margarine.
Line with graham cracker crumbs, pressing onto bottom and sides of pan with a teaspoon.
Let set in refrigerator.
With electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar until blended.
Add beaten egg yolks, light cream, vanilla and lemon rind to creamed mixture.
Beat until blended. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into crumb lined pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Let cool in oven for 1 hour.
Remove; cool in refrigerator.

title: four-day cake
directions: Follow directions for layer cake. Cool. Can use 8 or 9-inch pans.
Slice each layer in half to make four layers.
Mix powdered sugar, sour cream, coconut, vanilla and Cool Whip for filling. Spread between layers, on top and on sides of cake.
Put in airtight container.
Place in refrigerator for 4 days.
Do not peek.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Finely chop onion, green pepper and garlic clove; put in a large baking pan, stirring frequently.
For best results, use Washington Boro Jetstar tomatoes.
Bake at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and dice squash.
Cook with onion until tender; mash well.
Add butter, bread crumbs, grated cheese, salt and pepper. Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift the flour with soda and salt.
Cream the shortening and peanut butter with the sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Chill.
Roll in small balls the size of hickory nut.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put on the Kisses and put back in oven for 2 to 4 minutes longer.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: baked bear paws
directions: Brown the paws in a skillet with margarine.
Transfer to a casserole and season with salt, thyme, cinnamon and pepper.
Fry onion in the fat until softened and transfer the contents of the pan over the paws.
Add beef bouillon and lay the bacon over the top.
Cover and bake at 325° until tender.

title: pineapple sandwich mixture
directions: Bring egg, sugar, flour and juice from pineapple to boil Stirring constantly.
Let mixture cool
Add drained pineapple and 1/2 cup mayonnaise.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Microwave green beans as directed on package.
Drain well.
Add mushrooms and onions to reserved drippings in skillet.
Cook 10 minutes, drain.
Add bacon, green beans and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Microwave cheese as directed, pour over bean mixture.
Top with 2 tablespoons reserved bacon.
Serves 10.

title: scalded cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Put oil or shortening in heavy skillet on top of stove.
Get real hot.
Pour boiling water over meat mixture until soupy; stir well.
Add egg; beat well.
Pour in hot grease.
Let cook on top of stove until several air bubbles are in bread.
Put in a 450° oven; bake until lightly browned on top.

title: sopaipilla cheesecake
directions: Press 1 can of crescent rolls into bottom of 9 X 13 pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Spread over rolls in pan.
Cover with other can of rolls.
Melt butter and stir in rest of sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sandy's frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with juices and pour into square dish and freeze. Take out of freezer 10 minutes before serving and cut into squares. Can be doubled, but use a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: southern cornbread stuffing
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, melt bacon drippings until hot.
Add celery and onions.
Cook over medium-low heat until tender.
Stir in stuffing mix, cornbread, pecans and seasonings. Add eggs and toss lightly.
Pour hot broth over entire mixture. Toss.
Makes about 14 cups, about 220 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: parmesan tomato bake
directions: Combine tomatoes and corn starch. Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened.
Stir in onions.
Pour vegetables into one quart casserole.
Combine cheese, egg and salt. Mix well. Spoon rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture around the edge of the casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package.
Cook hamburger, onions and mushrooms.
Mix hamburger with macaroni, onions and mushrooms.
Layer of macaroni and cheese, layer of pizza sauce, layer of pepperoni, layer of Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a large casserole (3 quarts).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornbread mix.
Add last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot. Do not overbake.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add eggs, beating after each until smooth. Cover.
Chill for 2 hours.
Pour into hot, shallow pan with drippings.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: my favorite dinner roll
directions: Soften yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Stir in beaten egg.
Add dry milk.
Beat in as much flour as possible and then continue to add enough to make a soft dough, kneading 8 to 10 minutes.
Put into a large bowl that has been oiled, turning dough to coat it all over.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together in bowl, sprinkle on top of dough 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour. Bake in oblong pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in very large pot or bowl.
Store in large plastic or glass container with lid.
To use, measure 1/3 to 1/2 cup of mix into mug.
Add hot water to fill cup.

title: jello salad and cream topping
directions: Mix jello according to package and add fruit; let set.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in small amount boiling water until tender.
In saucepan, melt oleo, blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Combine sauce with drained vegetables.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna cookies
directions: Blend tuna, eggs and shortening.
Add Bisquick.
Blend and add just enough milk to make a thick batter.
Drop by spoonfuls on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gwen's taco dish
directions: Brown the ground beef until crumbly; drain the fat.
Combine the beef, soups, and enchilada sauce.
Cut the corn tortillas into halves or fourths; place on the bottom of a 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish.
Add ground beef mixture; then a layer of onion, green pepper, and beans.
On top of that a layer of cheddar cheese.
Repeat the layers, beginning with tortilla pieces and ending with cheese.
Place a ring of tortillas cut into halves around the edges of the baking dish on top of the cheese layer. (These will brown and crisp during baking.)
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve with lettuce and tomatoes, and/or rice on the side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture and set aside.
Combine egg, yogurt, butter and lemon juice; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until just moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and, while warm, prick tops with a toothpick; pour glaze over muffins.
Yield: 16 muffins.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook bacon and sausage until done.
Put on paper towel to drain all grease possible.
Crumble bacon and sausage and set aside.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package, drain.
Use big heavy pot.
Put noodles in and mix egg well, then add your milk.
Heat on low to medium until warm.
Add meat and salt to taste.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: grilled marinated chicken breasts
directions: In a medium bowl whisk together the lemon juice, oil, onion, salt, thyme and mustard.
With a sharp knife, score both sides of each breast in a crosshatch pattern, about 1/8-inch deep.
Pour 1/3 of the marinade into a shallow glass bowl.
Add half the chicken in a single layer and cover with another third of the marinade.
Put in the remaining breasts and cover with remaining marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Bring chicken to room temperature.
Preheat broiler and grill chicken 3 minutes each side.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan and make 3 holes for liquid.
Over all pour 2 cups cold water.
Mix with fork until well blended (no lumps).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam or greased.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: crazy cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, mix the first 8 ingredients in order given.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into quarters and layer on bottom of greased casserole dish. Arrange a layer of chicken, olives, onions and cheese.
Repeat a layer.
Mix soups and pour over top.
Let soak through.
Top with more cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice. Cook broccoli, then drain of excess water. Heat soup and cheese together until cheese is melted.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, 1 cup granulated sugar and 1 c water.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together shortening, 1 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and 3 eggs.
In another bowl, mix flour and baking soda.
Add this to sugar, brown sugar and eggs mixture.
Pour in vanilla.
Divide into balls and roll each one out.
Spread the date mixture over rolled out balls.
Roll each one up in a jelly roll.
Slice and bake at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a covered casserole in a moderate 350° oven until liquids are absorbed.

title: funeral salad
directions: Boil the gelatine, pineapple and sugar and cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Whip, then add Cool Whip.
Combine ingredients and place in an 8-inch square container.
Chill.

title: vegetable pizza bars(appetizer)
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch jelly roll pan with crescent rolls, pinching pieces together to form a crust.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry packet of Ranch dressing together.
Spread on top of crust.
Put veggies on top and gently press into cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Serve cold.
Cut into bars.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, flour, oatmeal and spices.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Peel and slice apples into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add apple juice.
Sprinkle sugar/flour mixture over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until top is nicely browned and apples are bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use double boiler.
Put 6 egg yolks in pan with flour.
Mix. Add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Just when you give up hope, it thickens.
Also, your tastebuds may require more or less sugar.
Layer dish with wafers, bananas, pudding, wafers, bananas and pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: southwestern tortilla wedges
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix fresh tomato salsa and sour cream. Reserve half of the salsa mixture.
Mix the remaining salsa mixture, half of the bell pepper and the chicken.
Place 2 tortillas on ungreased cookie sheet and spread with chicken mixture.
Spread 2 tortillas with guacamole and place on chicken mixture.
Spread 2 more tortillas with refried beans and place on guacamole.
Top each stack with remaining salsa, a tortilla, bell pepper and cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and filling is hot.
Cut each stack into 8 wedges.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Cream the butter. Add salt and part of the sugar gradually, blending well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Add rest of sugar alternately with milk until frosting is smooth and thick enough to spread.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk, then flour, sifted with salt, baking powder and spices. Roll thin.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Fry in hot oil or grease.

title: corn-spoon
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff.
Beat yolks until thick.
Stir corn meal and salt into milk, beating hard.
Cook a few seconds until consistency of thick mush; blend in margarine, corn, baking powder, egg yolks, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until puffy and golden brown (knife inserted in middle comes out clean).

title: "halo-halo"
directions: In a tall, wide glass, put 1 tablespoon each of the first 6 ingredients.
Fill the rest of the glass with shaved or crushed ice.
Pour 1/4 cup cream or milk over the ice.
Top with a scoop of ice cream, if desired, and serve.

title: rolled stuffed round steak
directions: Wipe steak with damp towel.
Trim excess fat.
Scar surface in diamond pattern 1/8-inch drop on both sides.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in Dutch oven.
Add celery and onion; saute until tender; remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning, marjoram and pepper, tossing lightly with fork until well mixed.
Place stuffing lengthwise down center of steak; start at narrow end, roll up and secure with skewers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown steak in Dutch oven.
Spoon mushrooms and liquids over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Make gravy.
Cut crosswise and pour on gravy.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand until dough starts to rise. Place in refrigerator, covered.
When ready to use, remove and roll out in desired shape.
Let stand until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, sliced mushrooms, onion rings and sliced celery in a large bowl; set aside.

title: pineapple pistachio pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into molds or whatever and refrigerate.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Put graham cracker crust in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over crust and chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Line a large casserole dish with tortilla chips.
Spread lettuce over chips and sprinkle on 3/4 cup onions.
On top of this, spread a layer of refried beans, a layer of guacamole and then a layer of sour cream. Sprinkle grated cheese over the sour cream and garnish with remaining onions.
This may be served hot or cold with remaining tortilla chips and, if you prefer it spicier, you can add chopped jalapeno peppers.

title: bran-n-date bread
directions: Grease loaf pan, 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch.
Blend ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: buttered honey chicken bites
directions: Chill the chicken pieces overnight.
Melt butter and honey in a small saucepan.
Add teriyaki.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Dip each into butter-honey-teriyaki sauce and roll in sesame seed.
Place chicken pieces on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, turning once to brown evenly. Reheat remaining sauce to serve with cooked pieces of chicken. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: fruit filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice dough into 24 (1/8-inch) slices. Refrigerate remaining dough.
Place slices 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Spread each slice with 1/2 teaspoon of jam to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Set aside.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in large saucepan.
Mix together flour, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir into meat mixture. Add onion, tomatoes and water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir evaporated milk into mixture. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes six 1/2-cup servings.

title: fudge ice cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat about 4 to 5 minutes until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool according to directions on back of cake mix box.

title: "i hate to cook" goulash
directions: Crumble and cook hamburger in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and let brown.
Add beans and ketchup.
Let simmer a few minutes and serve over toast.
Cheap, quick and easy!

title: brownie pizza
directions: Grease pizza pan.
Mix brownie mix and eggs according to directions.
Add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts to mix.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk; set aside.
Spread peanut butter over cooled brownie, then spread pudding, Cool Whip and finally add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and chocolate bar shavings.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved and syrupy.
Mix the eggs, flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda good.
Combine and mix good all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute beef, salt and onion in skillet.
Drain and let cool.
In a large salad bowl, place lettuce, beef, grated cheese, corn chips and dressing; mix thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange concentrate. Mix in fruit.
Put in mold if desired.
Rinse mold with cold water before filling.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil, fruit sweetener, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in pineapple.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to blended mixture.
Stir in coconut, carrots and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Serves 24.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour in pastry shell.
Put berries on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together sugar, flour, salt, cream cheese, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Fold in whipped cream and then egg whites.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Cool in oven for one hour.

title: spinach ricotta dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place spinach and onion in small saucepan with small amount of water.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Beat cheeses and seasonings in small mixing bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in spinach mixture and spread into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with tomato and Parmesan cheese. Serve with crisp rye crackers or bagel chips.
Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In a medium saute pan, cook onion and garlic until onion is translucent.
Add tomato sauce; cook for 5 minutes on low heat and then add zucchini.
Cook for about 15 minutes.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in all ingredients, adding enough flour to make firm dough that's easy to handle.
Turn into greased bowl so greased side is up.
Let rise to double (about 1 hour).
Punch down; divide into half.
Flatten each half, rolling into a rectangle.
Fold in two sides and roll up tightly into a loaf.
Place in greased bread pan; brush top with margarine.
Let rise to double (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cover for softer crust.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add rest of ingredients.
Batter is good for up to 6 weeks when kept covered in
the refrigerator.
Use as needed with
muffin cups and pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Hot muffins anytime!

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Put onion and pepper through food processor. Add all ingredients.
Blend with mixer at slow speed. Will keep for weeks and improves with age.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Pour beans into container and rinse off juice from beans. Drain.
Add ketchup and chopped onions together. Mix.
Add rinsed beans to mixture. Put into a baking dish.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and broil until bacon is brown.

title: betty's doughnuts
directions: Mix into dough.
Roll out and cut into doughnuts.
Fry in deep fat.

title: biblical fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 1/2-inch tube pan.
Chop almonds, raisins and figs fine.
Flour them well with part of the 2 cups of flour. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; set aside.
In mixing bowl, blend butter, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Sift in flour and baking powder; add water and honey.
Stir in floured nuts and fruits; beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cook rhubarb in water.
Add marshmallows, 1 cup sugar and jello.
Stir well.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and bananas. Stir in sour cream.
Sift together salt, flour and baking soda. Mix everything together.
Pour into greased loaf pans and sprinkle with brownsugar.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Put vanilla wafers flat side down in muffin papers in muffin tins.
Pour half full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool before peeling off paper.
Top with pie filling (cherry, blueberry, etc.).

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted margarine evenly over all. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour. Yields one (13 x 9 x 2-inch) cake.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil butter, brown sugar and milk 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add powdered sugar.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, then beat vigorously by hand for about 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Blend garlic powder and melted margarine.
The minute the biscuits come from the oven, brush with garlic butter.
Serve immediately.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour
cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage ball
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use toothpicks to pick them up.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugars and flour.
Blend in melted butter. Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: Brown turkey and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add remainder of ingredients and heat through.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Quarter margarine in bowl and add water (boiling).
Stir in oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt into mixture and beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato pot pie
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions in 2 tbsp. dressing over med.
heat. Add flour and seasoning.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened. Stir in vegetables and1 c.
cheese.
Cook 5 minutes. Spoon mixture into 1 1/2 qt.
casserole.
Stir 1/2 c. dressing into potatoes.
Top casserole with potato mixture, broil until golden.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, broil until cheese begins to melt.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine candied fruit to make 4 cups (your choice), or cut back to 1 or 2 cups fruit.

title: aunt betty's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Transfer mixture to 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more. Remove from oven and drain excess fat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: adobe bread(brought up from ft. sutter in sacramento.)
directions: Add salt, cream, sugar and oil to warm potatoes.
Cool before adding flour.
Chill.
Divide into balls and roll out one at a time, as thin as possible, adding flour as needed.
Bake on medium to hot griddle, turning often, until done.

title: the sting of the bee
directions: Break eggs and separate yolks.
Beat the whites; add sugar slowly.
Add yolks, butter, milk and flour.
Bake it for about 20 to 30 minutes (medium temperature).
After it's ready, cut it in half horizontally.

title: whole wheat pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together oil, water and salt. Stir in flour.
Roll out and place in oiled pie pan.
Prebake 8 minutes.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Add to raisins and cook, stirring until clear.
Remove from heat and stir in vinegar and butter. Turn into pastry.
Line pan and cover with top pastry or lattice strips.
Bake at 425° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour; add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn. Beat; stir in peppers and onions.
Pour in half batter; sprinkle 1/2 cheese.
Repeat and bake at 375°.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook water and raisins until raisins are done, 3 to 5 minutes. Cool and add flour sifted with soda and pinch of salt.
Add remaining spices.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Place in loaf pan or Pyrex dish and ice with powdered sugar frosting.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender and cut up.
Simmer with celery, carrots, onion, salt and pepper in boiling water.
Save chicken broth.
Combine rice, chicken, mushrooms, pimiento and 3/4 cup almonds.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour and 2 cups chicken broth.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly. Add marjoram and thyme.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Turn into an 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and remaining almonds.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with gravy made from remaining chicken broth, if desired.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix and cook first 6 ingredients 15 minutes and cool.
Then mix flour and soda with other ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes or until sides turn loose from sides at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat, then saute onion and bell pepper.
Season to taste.
In about a 9 x 12-inch dish, layer shredded cabbage, washed rice, then meat.
Mix the soup and 1/4 cup of water and pour over casserole.
Mix the tomato sauce and 1/2 cup of water and pour over casserole.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground meat and onion until browned. Drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry), tomato, picante sauce and corn. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Put in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add nuts, if desired.
In another bowl, mix the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Add both mixtures together and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or so.

title: karo syrup casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed;
put in large casserole.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix
butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla and shape into balls.
Dip
them in melted chocolate and wax with toothpick.

title: million dollar pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and nuts; blend well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: hot lettuce
directions: Mix, then add water to desired amount.
Boil and pour on crisp, clean lettuce.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and spices in saucepan.
Heat until very hot.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate and chill thoroughly.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Grease an 8-inch pan lightly.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red pepper conserve
directions: Grind, chop or process peppers.
Add sugar and vinegar. Simmer until thick.
Freeze.
To serve, mix with cream cheese or cottage cheese.
May be used as dip or sauce over vegetables.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in mashed bananas and lemon extract. Stir in nuts.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cake tests done.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until good and done.
Take out of pot to cool. Do not pour broth out of pot.
After the chicken is cool, pick off bone and return to broth.
Bring back to a boil.
Cut tortillas into strips then into bite size pieces. Put into broth and chicken.
After all has been added turn to medium low and add cream of chicken soup, let cook about 5 to 10 minutes, then it is ready to eat.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown meat; drain and add onion and green pepper.
Mix in taco seasoning and soup.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Spread sour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, salt and baking powder using electric mixer.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off (do not scoop or sift flour).
Add flour to butter mixture.
Blend until fine crumbs form.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator for up to 4 weeks.
Makes 8 cups of mix.

title: peanut butter fudge - weight watchers
directions: Cream peanut butter, honey and vanilla.
Add milk and stir. Knead like bread and press in pan lined with foil.
Chill and cut into 4 pieces.
(One provides 1 1/2 protein, 1/2 milk, 1 1/2 shortening and 30 optional calories.)

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate up to 4 chicken breasts for 3 hours or more. Add 2 tablespoons of molasses to marinade to baste with while cooking.

title: one rise rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix water, sugar and dry yeast.
Let sit until mixture bubbles.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn out onto floured surface, knead.
Pat out.
Cut into rolls.
Place on greased 9 x 13-inch pan and brush tops of rolls with oils.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat; add spaghetti sauce, sugar, salt, chili powder and mushrooms.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix sour cream, onions and cream cheese.
Layer noodles, meat mixture, cheese mixture, etc., ending with noodles.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.

title: microwave cheesy black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mash peas (or use food processor) and combine with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart micro-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 or 4 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring several times. Serve warm with chips.

title: chocolate milkshake
directions: Mix and shake well.

title: upside-down apple cake
directions: Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon. Beat eggs and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together. Add water to egg and sugar.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Butter pan good.
Add part of cinnamon and sugar mixture in bottom of pan.
Add apples and rest of sugar mixture.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Take from oven and turn upside down.

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Fry sausage and onion, making sure sausage is well broken up. Drain grease.
Add artichoke hearts that are well drained and mashed.
Add cheese and bread crumbs.
Stir well and cook a few minutes.
Cool slightly and then add eggs, one at a time, and stir thoroughly after each.
Cook again for a few minutes, stirring constantly.

title: very carne chile
directions: Trim fat.
Set oven to 300°.
Put brisket in roaster.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 1/2 hours.

title: quick and delicious salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve in a lettuce lined bowl. Garnish with herb flavored croutons.
Serves 6.

title: hot dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until well blended.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter and put in Worcestershire sauce.
Mix together Corn Chex, Wheat Chex, Rice Chex, Bugles, pretzels and nuts in large pan.
Spoon a little mixture of butter and Worcestershire sauce over Chex's etc., and put in oven.
Every 15 minutes or so, pour some of the butter mixture over cereal and sprinkle some of salt on top (or package mix).
Mix well and return to oven.
Repeat about 4 times.
Don't get too brown.
Let cool on paper towels and store in quart jars.
Makes about 14 to 16 quarts.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash vegetables, shred lettuce, set aside.
Chop onions with tops and celery.
Drain peas and set aside.

In large bowl, layer lettuce 1/2 inch thick, next green onions, layer sweet peas, celery, bacon bites, cheese and spread mayonnaise or Miracle Whip. Repeat order of ingredients until used up or depending on the size of salad you want.
You may use more or less mayonnaise on a layer or reduced or light mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.
Ham or chopped chicken or turkey breast may be substituted for bacon bites.

title: chicken-pepper-steak
directions: With a very sharp knife, cut chicken breasts in strips 1/8 inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic; set aside. Heat oil in a large frying pan or wok.
Add chicken.
Cook until tender.
Add soy sauce, garlic and ginger; let simmer about 15 minutes.
Add vegetables; toss until vegetables are tender-crisp. Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve with fluffy rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix evaporated milk, sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan and bring to boiling.
Stir and boil for 7 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour boiling mixture over all.
Beat until fudge is creamy.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan to cool.
Cut into squares when cold.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, milk and flavorings.
Beat well, mixing slowly.
Bake in a tube cake pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven on when cake goes in the oven.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan which has been coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cook.
Cover with strawberry glaze and strawberries and top with Cool Whip.

title: nestle toll house cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Combine yeast with milk, shortening and salt.
Mix.
Stir in 2 cups flour and mix.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a moderately soft but not sticky dough.
Knead on floured surface. Knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn once.
Let rise until double (1 1/4 hours), covered.
Punch down, cover and let rise until double again (45 minutes).
Shape in loaves and place in 2 well-greased or oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
If bread browns too fast, cover loosely with foil the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon removing bones and skin.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, and spices.
Chill several hours.
Shape mixture into an 8 x 2-inch log.
Roll in nuts.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Cook bacon crisp and crumble it.
Mix together the onion, broccoli, cauliflower, raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.
Mix together the following to make a dressing:
sugar, vinegar and the 3/4 cup combination.
Add the dressing to the vegetables and stir.

title: cream of mushroom soup(low-fat)
directions: Add oil to a medium saucepan and saute onions and garlic until onions are translucent.
Add mushrooms and 1/4 cup flour.
Add water, bouillon cubes, bay leaf, pepper and salt.
Let it come to a boil and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add skim milk, then mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and add to soup. Cook until thickened.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in loaf pan. Spread barbecue sauce on top. Cook in microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients except chocolate and paraffin.
Mix well and roll into small balls (marble size). Chill until hard (place on greased pan).

title: rocky road pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping, chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in skillet and drain. Grate cheese.
Add sausage and mix well.
Add the Bisquick mix. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for about 13 minutes or until lightly golden.
Yields about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Make into small balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hash browns
directions: Cut potatoes into cube size pieces.
Cut onion into small pieces.
Spray shallow pan with Pam.
Place cut potatoes on pan and spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then put into broiler until golden brown.

title: chocolate 'n biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients on medium heat until lumps are out and mix starts to thicken.
When thickened, add vanilla.

title: shells and vegetable dish
directions: Mix vegetables and pasta and add butter or margarine and cheese.
Cook in microwave until cheese is melted.
Add garlic salt or salt to taste.

title: chinese rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add rice and stir until golden. Add onions, green pepper and celery.
When vegetables are limp, add soy sauce.
Add chicken stock and nuts.
Cover and cook until rice is fluffy and the moisture is absorbed or this can be baked in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
This freezes well.
Serves 4.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixer and add eggs, one at a time. Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes in an unbaked pie crust.

title: cereal candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper, using tablespoon to drop.
Put in freezer for 10 minutes.
This will keep for 2 to 3 weeks in a tine or you can keep it frozen.
Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving.
(Toasted pecans may be used instead of peanuts.)

title: courtney and mom's stuffed peppers
directions: In saucepan, blanch green peppers for 3 minutes.

title: toasted pecan ice cream sauce(15 minutes)
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except pecans. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (6 to 8 minutes).
Just before serving, stir in pecans.
Serve warm or cool over ice cream, cake, pancakes or waffles.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: dividend casserole
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onions in margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in meat and parsley.
Add gravy and season to taste.
Turn into casserole dish.
Combine milk with cheese; add biscuit mix and blend well.
Knead gently about 10 times on lightly floured board, roll into rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 6 squares and place on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are golden.
In this casserole you can use any meat you have on hand, beef, lamb, veal or pork.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown (saute) onion and pepper; add meat (stir-fry).
Add other ingredients.
Pour in greased 2 quart casserole baking dish, cover and bake at 350° for one hour (take off the lid the last 15 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl (large).
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and chocolate cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and stay 15 minutes before it can be cut easily.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni and "pink" cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as you normally would.
In separate small pot, put 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chopped garlic; let simmer for 2 minutes.
Add entire can of tomato sauce.
Drain macaroni and return it to pot, then add tomato sauce and garlic mixture plus stir in the Ricotta cheese.
Stir over low heat until hot.
Serve! Serves 6.
Great alone or as a side dish.

title: working gal's quick apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the 3/4 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Arrange apples by pressing lightly onto batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburger meat and 1 or 2 onions.
Break up hamburger with fork; add salt and pepper.
Drain off grease and place in long cake pan.
Add to pan celery soup, chicken soup, vegetables, milk and rice.
Stir up mixture.
This makes a large casserole (the rice will absorb what may seem like too much liquid).
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: french fries for 100
directions: Fifty-five fresh potatoes will yield 45 pounds of French fry potatoes.
Soak cut potatoes in cold water.
Drain as ready to fry. Fry in deep-fat at 350° until brown.

title: cherry pineapple dump cake
directions: Dump cherries and pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle box of dry cake mix on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top of this.
Melt butter or margarine; pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In large baking dish put rice in and add green beans with liquid.
Add Cream of mushroom soup.
Add water and then add the pork chops.
If the pork chops are not covered with the liquid add more water to cover.
Use black pepper & creole seasoning to taste. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and onions.
Combine with salt and cover with ice.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and spices.
Drain cucumbers and onions.
Add to vinegar mixture. Heat slowly to scald.
Do not boil! Seal in jars.
Wait 48 hours before opening.

title: quick chicken saute
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in seasoned flour, shaking off excess. In skillet, heat fat.
Saute chicken, turning once, until cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Add more fat to pan if necessary, then add onion and garlic.
Add pepper and saute a few minutes.
Add carrots, sauteing a few minutes, then zucchini, until each is tender.
Return chicken to pan.
Sprinkle on herbs, salt and pepper; add wine and cover, sauteing for several more minutes until chicken is hot and ingredients are blended.
A light gravy should result; add more liquid if necessary.
Delicious with pasta or rice.

title: chocolate lush
directions: First Layer:
Mix walnuts, butter and flour; mix and spread in cake pan until golden brown.

title: hot cheddar cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into baking dish, sprinkle extra shredded Cheddar on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with wax paper.
(You don't need to cover the sides.)
Grease wax paper with margarine or shortening.
Mix ingredients together; pour in center of the pan. Spread to about 9 x 13 inches.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes at 375°, until surface looks dry and no longer sticky.
(Wax paper will smoke some.)
Invert onto a tea towel covered with powdered sugar.
Peel off wax paper.
Roll cake in tea towel lengthwise until cool.
When cool, unroll carefully and spread filling.

title: cinnamon-apple syrup for pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat through and serve over pancakes.

title: cherry yum-yum(1953)
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Add cracker crumbs and press to line bottom of dish.
Place Dream Whip in cool bowl and add milk. Whip until peaks form.
Add softened cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet; saute onions over low heat, stirring constantly until golden color.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, mix together onions, ground beef, ground pork, bread crumbs, milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Make into meatballs the size of large walnuts.
Return to skillet; brown meatballs on all sides.
Cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes or until done.
Makes about 20 meatballs.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion and Veg-All in the chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Use 1 well rounded teaspoonful to 1 cup hot water (or to suit taste).

title: yum yum chicken
directions: Mix all together except stuffing and melted oleo.
Let set; cover with stuffing and melted oleo.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels over double boiler with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter and 3/4 evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 of cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. After 15 minutes is up, take out of oven and spread with melted caramels.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add together all the ingredients, saving 1/2 package of dressing mix for topping.
Place into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with dressing mix before baking.

title: sauce hollandaise
directions: Melt 12 tablespoons butter and set aside, keeping it warm. In separate saucepan, whisk egg yolks until thick, then beat in the tablespoon lemon juice.
Place that pan over low heat and stir in the 1 tablespoon hard butter.
When blended, remove pan from low heat and beat in cream; add melted butter slowly. Whisk constantly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mexican hot---mexican hot
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and onions.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer a few more minutes. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: prune cake with buttermilk icing
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs, sifted flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and allspice together.
Add buttermilk to the egg mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish, lightly greased with butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use Buttermilk Icing.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix in potato chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 to 8 dozen cookies.
I usually only get 6 dozen.

title: hot sauce
directions: Dice peppers, green onions and tomatillo. Add to stewed tomatoes. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: simple simon spareribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs and arrange single layer in shallow pan.
Combine wine, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over ribs. Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours; baste occasionally. Serves 4 to 5.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring sugar and 2 cups water to boil.
Add jello and allow to cool.
Add the rest of the water, almond extract and pineapple juice.
Mix well and freeze.
Remove from the freezer 4 hours before serving.
The mixture will become slushy.
Do not thaw too much.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: beef kabobs(low-fat)
directions: Cut beef into small cubes.
Place beef in glass dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over beef.
Marinate for 1 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Alternate beef and vegetables on 6 kabobs.
Bake at 350° to desired doneness (10 minutes for rare to 20 minutes for well).

title: dill crackers(appetizer)
directions: In pan, heat oil; add dill weed, lemon salt and dressing mix. Spoon over crackers and gently mix.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all together and beat for 3 minutes.
Add poppy seed. Bake in 2 greased tins at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinade for roast beef
directions: Marinate roast overnight, turning once.

title: microwaved scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and put in casserole dish. Blend soup, milk, onion and butter and pour over potatoes. Cook on High 19 to 24 minutes. Stir every 4 to 5 minutes and last 2 minutes, put cheese on top to melt. Cook, covered, but remove lid when cheese is added. Standing time 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in a sprayed 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Add onions and green pepper to hot browned meat mixture.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through and put on crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Layer pepperoni and cheese between two pizza crust. Bake at 350 degrees until crust is golden brown. Don't cut until completely cool.

title: madras pork chops and rice
directions: Brown meat slowly in skillet.
Combine soup, curry powder and water.
Place rice in bottom of buttered baking dish or shallow casserole.
Place browned pork chops on top of rice.
Pour sauce over pork chops and rice.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: You will need 1 greased 9-inch pie plate.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place cut sides down in casserole dish.
Add 1/2-inch hot water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
When cooled, carefully scoop out pulp and mash with potato masher.
(This should yield about 2 cups.)
Stir squash together with oranges, margarine, flavoring and spice.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir beaten yolks into squash mixture.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold in squash mixture.
Spoon into 6 ungreased (6 ounce) souffle dishes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Sprinkle each with toasted almonds and serve immediately.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello.
Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package, only using 1 1/2 boiling water.
Let set.

title: malted milk ball pie
directions: Combine ice cream, whipped topping and 1 cup crushed balls. Fold together.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Sprinkle remaining candy on top.
Freeze.

title: fluffy vanilla walnut pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, pudding mix, sweet milk and Cool Whip together with mixer.
Add some walnuts.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust; sprinkle with walnuts.
Chill.

title: mixed sausages bites
directions: In 12-inch skillet over high heat, heat Italian sausage links and 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover skillet over medium heat.
Brown sausages well. Cut sausage into 1-inch diagonal slices.
Set aside.
Cook German sausages; cut crosswise 3/4-inch pieces.
Cook frankfurters until they curl.
Add cocktail frankfurters and orange marmalade.
Cook until mixture is heated through.
Serve in chafing dish with cocktail picks.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: In large bowl stir together real mayonnaise, cheese, milk, onion, red pepper and pepper.
Add tuna, peas and macaroni; toss to coat well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
In small saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 300° about 45 to 60 minutes.
Forms a crust.

title: spiced pork chops
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; dredge pork chops.
In a skillet, brown chops in oil on both sides.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian roast - crock-pot
directions: Put everything in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Easy; really good meal.

title: sweet and sour pork on rice
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Let cool, dice them.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and water, coat diced pieces of pork.
Fry in wok or frying pan 8-10 minutes.

title: aunt wanda's chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup milk and mix until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat while stirring.
Boil and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
With fork, beat eggs with remaining cup of milk.
Gradually stir into hot mixture, then put back over heat.
Bring back to a boil while stirring and boil until mixture thickens, usually about a minute. Remove from heat, stir in butter, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until chips melt.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Spread with whipped cream.

title: mocha fudge pie
directions: Combine hot water and 2 teaspoons coffee granules in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Add brownie mix, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg whites; stir until well blended.
Pour in a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 22 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. In food storage plastic bad, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate dough into 16 biscuits; cut each into quarters.
Place dough pieces in bag, and shake to coat.
Arrange pieces in bottom of greased pan.
Arrange raisins among biscuit pieces.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and margarine; mix well.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake for 33 to 37 minutes or until golden brown and biscuits are no longer doughy in center.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto a serving plate.
Serve warm.
Pull apart for serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Put layer of chicken in baking dish.
Cover with crushed Doritos.
Bring Ro-Tel to a boil in saucepan.
Add Cheddar cheese soup; heat and add sour cream.
Pour over chips.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roast pork fried rice
directions: Use leftover or cooked rice.
Dice roast pork and onion.
Wash bean sprouts and remove tails, if you have the patience.
Using a huge flame, heat pan and add oil and salt.
Scramble egg.
Next, add onion, bean sprouts and pork.
Add sherry and stock and cover for 45 seconds.
Add rice and break up clumps.
Cover for 45 seconds.
Uncover; stir thoroughly.
Next, add soy sauce and other dry ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
You may add minced scallion for color.
If you do, add as you turn off flame and stir in.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Empty one can of beans in greased casserole.
Combine sugar and mustard and sprinkle 1/2 over beans.
Top with remaining beans and add remaining sugar and mustard mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel jello
directions: To melted butter, add 3 teaspoons sugar.
Stir.
Hand mix well with pretzels in bowl.
Pour and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar, folding in Cool Whip.
Spread cream cheese onto cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; add frozen strawberries.
Mix well.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes; pour on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate to set.

title: easy vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put ground beef along with the rest of the ingredients in a pot on high.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to medium and cook until the potato is soft.

title: sunday morning fried apples
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.
Leave skin on.
Slice lengthwise (not too thinly).
Use a large frying pan so you will only have a few layers.
Put some butter (optional) or add water (enough to cover the bottom) to the frying pan.
Let the water boil (medium-high heat).
Use of water instead of butter reduces fat. Add slices in 1 layer.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add second layer.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon.
When bottom layer browns/caramelizes, flip over and brown top layer.

title: oven stew
directions: Chop vegetables; mix everything raw and put in roaster (you can brown meat first or put in raw).
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in water until tender.
Do not add salt.
Drain. Melt butter in small pan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly. Cook, stirring constantly, until blended.

Grate cheese and put 1 cup of cheese aside for topping of casserole. Add remaining grated cheese to milk, cooking and stirring until melted. Blend together cheese sauce and macaroni; place in casserole dish. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over macaroni casserole. Bake in a 325° oven until cheese on top is browned.

title: grandma nadyne's sirloin tips
directions: In large casserole dish pour soups over beef and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Enjoy with mashed potatoes and broccoli with melted cheese.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: creamy venison
directions: Pound steak to tenderize.
Cut into pieces.
Flour and brown on both sides.
Put pieces of steak in a casserole dish.
Make a thin gravy in pan steak was browned in.
Pour over steak and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: mrs. frank graham's pound cake(mother of rev. billy graham)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat butter, sugar and egg mixture thoroughly.
Blend in flour, sifted with salt and baking powder,
gradually, mixing well.
Add mace and blend thoroughly.
Then slowly add heavy cream and mix well.
Turn batter into large 10-inch tube pan and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until browned.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Good on baked chicken.

title: cherry or cranberry cashew cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour or baking soda, gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, milk chips, dried cherries or cranberries and cashews.
Drop by rounded tablespoons on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: big batch muffins(low-fat)
directions: Can reduce sugar or fructose, oil and eggs for low-fat.

title: easy pizzas
directions: Cover half of an English muffin with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the sauce.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.

title: diet blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook together blackberries, cornstarch and water.
Add enough Equal packages to suit your taste.
Cook until thick.
Use flour and butter.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and add to first mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin pans with cooking spray. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and ginger in a bowl.
Mix carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla with a wire whip or fork in a separate bowl.
Stir flour mixture into carrot mixture. Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from muffin pans.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, adding more water if needed. Remove cover and continue cooking until most of the liquid has evaporated and mixture is thick.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coleslaw salad
directions: Toast almonds until lightly brown.
Mix slaw, almonds, sunflower seeds and noodles.
Mix oil, water, vinegar, sugar and flavor packet from noodles.
Pour dressing over salad 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside. Mix all other ingredients well. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in two or three 9-inch pans.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve cold with lettuce.

title: candy trifles
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot water, melt chocolate pieces.
Stir in nuts and noodles until well coated.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: custard
directions: Mix sugar in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour in metal ring or pan. Coat bottom and sides of pan as much as possible with sugar mixture.
Beat eggs.
Add condensed milk and warm water or milk. Pour into sugar coated pan.
Put this pan into a bigger pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
It is done when a knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and chop lettuce, then refrigerate.
Combine all ingredients except egg yolk, cheese and croutons.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add egg yolk and mix until thick.
Immediately add chilled lettuce, cheese and croutons.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in tight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Very good.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Then add remaining ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
Beat all together then add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss. Top with Fritos.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth (about 3 minutes with mixer).
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell and chill for about 3 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: slush-delush
directions: Stir all ingredients,
except
7-Up, in plastic bowl or container;
freeze
until solid.
When entertaining, spoon 1/3 cup or more of slush into glass and add 7-Up.
Garnish with a cherry or 1/2 orange slice.
Keep remaining slush frozen until ready to use again.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix above together.
Serve with cut-up fruit, such as strawberries, peaches, grapes and cantaloupe to dip.
Great for the summer!

title: crown casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently. Drain fat.
Add next 6 ingredients; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Flatten biscuits slightly and arrange overlapping around edge of casserole.
