Brush biscuits with mayonnaise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes
or until biscuits are browned.
(We like a little more mayonnaise, sometimes I precook vegetables.)

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Tenderize chicken breasts.
Place in a skillet on top of stove.
Cook until done.
Put chicken in a casserole dish; cover with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes.
Take out of oven; sprinkle Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Serve this over egg noodles.

title: grated carrots with apricots
directions: Melt butter; add onion and saute.
Add apricots and carrots; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add water and cook about 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add sherry, salt and pepper.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour in freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; dredge in cornstarch.
Brown lightly in oil.
Add green onions, garlic and water chestnuts; stir-fry.
Mix soy sauce, white wine and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and stir.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice; sprinkle with cashews.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak or ground chuck and onion in butter.
Stir in soup, water, sour cream, and paprika.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir often.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: ham and wild rice salad
directions: Combine water and wild rice in a medium saucepan and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed.

title: muncy onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.
Soak in ice water 2 hours.
Drain and dry.
Dip onions in batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil until brown.

title: crabmeat florentine
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine.
Add mushrooms and green pepper.
Add crabmeat and wine.
Cook until mixture is heated through and set aside.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Combine vinegar, mustard and salad dressing.
Add to cabbage mixture.

title: pesto puffs
directions: Roll out one sheet of dough to 11 x 14-inch size.
Spread sauce on dough and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll long side in jelly roll fashion and wrap tightly in Saran Wrap.
Freeze. Continue with second sheet.

title: dunbar macaroni
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Pour off excess grease. Mix other ingredients with beef in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil, stirring well.
Add carrots, pineapple, and nuts, beating after each addition.
Add sifted ingredients and stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost with whipped cream icing or cream cheese icing.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork, onion and salt; drain.
Combine bouillon, soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour over pork; simmer. Add pineapple and green peppers.
Simmer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and chopped nuts.
In mixer, blend sour cream, oil and eggs, one at a time.
Add butter flavoring.
Mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a well-greased and floured stem pan.

title: garlicky pesto pasta salad
directions: In a food processor, combine the packed basil, garlic, raw pine nuts and oil and puree until a uniform sauce results. Scrape the mixture into a bowl and stir in the grated cheese. Set aside. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil and cook the orzo until tender. Drain well, rinse, drain again and place in a large bowl. Toss with a couple of tablespoons of the reserved pesto dressing, or more to taste. Reserve any leftover pesto for another use. To serve, add the tomatoes and toasted pine nuts to the salad, toss with more pesto dressing and black pepper to taste, and scatter with fresh basil.

title: dixie dogs
directions: Mix first 5 (batter) ingredients with enough milk to make a cake-like batter.
Roll wieners in batter and drop into hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: oriental shrimp and rice
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Combine water and soy sauce in a large Dutch oven.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add rice; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons melted butter until crisp-tender.
Add shrimp and saute over medium heat 3 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Stir into rice.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Add eggs.
Cook without stirring until eggs begin to set on bottom.
Draw a spatula across bottom of pan to form large curds.
Continue until eggs are thickened, but still moist.
Do not stir constantly.
Stir eggs and pepper into rice mixture; toss gently.
Garnish, if desired.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Dredge gumdrops, raisins and nut meats in 2 cups flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 cups flour, seasonings, eggs and soda. Bake at 350° for 2 hours in angel food cake pan or 1 hour in two small pans.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water and sugar.
Stir together and put in freezer until slightly jelled.
Then mix with mixer until it turns pink.
Then mix Cool Whip and beaten egg whites in a bowl with spoon until completely mixed.
Mix Cool Whip and egg whites to jello mixture.
Mix well with spoon, then add drained pineapple.
Mix all together until light pink.
Pinch angel food cake in pieces and layer in bottom of pan, then pour half of mixture over cake.
Put another layer of cake and pour remaining mixture over cake.
Top with pecan halves.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned fruit cake(stack cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and separate into six balls and bake in 8-inch skillet about 15 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes six layer cake.
Use apple butter or apples stewed with allspice between each layer.
Best if let set couple days before serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put pineapple in large boiler and add jello powder.
Bring to a boil and set aside to cool (do not congeal).
When it is cool, add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.
You may use orange, strawberry, lime or lemon jello.
Congeal.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef and onion.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder, then add soup and cheese, cut in cubes.
Stir over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Then add vanilla, cinnamon and flour.
Next, add diced apples and walnuts; mix together well.
Pour into cake or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers in a greased casserole.
Mix and top with broken cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Sift the flour over the nuts before adding to the mixture.
(I chop nuts in food processor.)
Pour into greased tube pan and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and carrots; add dry ingredients. Drop from teaspoon onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Make powdered sugar icing, add real orange juice.
They are soft cookies and keep for about 3 weeks in a closed container.

title: orange pineapple sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Makes one gallon.

title: lazy man's peach pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients separately and pour into baking dish over melted butter.
Sprinkle mashed fruit over it.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk and eggs, then mix and beat.
Add strawberries, coconut and nuts.
Mix and beat well. Grease and flour three layer pans.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove cakes and cool thoroughly.

title: english pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Put well-drained asparagus in buttered baking dish.
Chop eggs and put layer over asparagus, then layer with grated cheese.
Add drained peas.
Dot peas and asparagus with butter and season with salt and pepper.
Add milk to soup; mix well and pour over top of all.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until bubbly all over and crackers crumbs brown (this can be cut in half).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Chill dough until firm.
Thinly slice 1/4 inch thick and lay in circles on greased pizza pan 1/4 inch apart.
Cookies will join during baking.
Bake as package directs.
Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over baked crust.

title: hot fudge syrup
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar. Add milk and butter. Cook over low flame until it starts to boil, then turn to medium and let boil 10 minutes.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Blend together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture, then fold in apples, raisins and nuts.
Mix well; pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Mix other ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slow until brown, about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: low-fat salmon loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and press into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: nut roll
directions: Scale 1/2 cup milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into milk mixture.
Stir well.
Blend in eggs and flour, mixing well.
Divide into 4 parts.
Turn out each part on a lightly floured board.
Roll into 16 x 12-inch rectangle. Brush dough with evaporated milk.
Spread each part with 1/4 of nut filling.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning at long side and brushing underneath of each roll with evaporated milk.
Seal edges and brush top with evaporated milk.
Place rolls on greased baking sheet and let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Slice when cool.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6)
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish and put 1/2 package of dressing mix on bottom.
Mix chicken, onion soup and milk; pour over dressing.
Use other dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and boil until almost done.
Pour in colander and drain well.
Spray casserole dish (12 x 7 1/2-inch or 8 x 8-inch) with Pam.
Spread Cheez Whiz over bottom of casserole dish.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in milk, coconut and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat for 40 minutes, covered.
Add milk and margarine and simmer for 30 more minutes on low.

title: cherry raisin coffee cake
directions: Spoon on cherry jam in small amounts.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still hot, drizzle with icing made from confectioners sugar, moistened with milk.

title: macaroni tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Let thicken.
Add tuna, olives and onion salt. Pour over cooked macaroni.
Bake in casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: soupas(portuguese soup)
directions: 1. Cook meat in water till tender. Do not drain, place meat and liquid in large pot.
2. Add all but mint. Add enough water to cover ingredients
and simmer 1-2 hours. Add mint and simmer 15-20 minutes
more.
3. Remove spice bag and mint.

title: daddy's chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in saucepan. Add enough milk to make a smooth paste. Add egg yolks.
Beat well. Stir in remaining milk and butter. Bring to a slow boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour into serving dishes. Chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar with eggs, margarine and oil.
Add vanilla and rest of dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate dough.
Make into small balls; flatten with small glass.
Put margarine and sugar on bottom of glass before flattening dough.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy oatmeal
directions: Combine oats, milk, raisins, sugar and salt in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Form 1-inch balls.
Bake 14 to 17 minutes in 400° oven.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool. Roll in sugar again.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Refrigerate.
Mix softened cream cheese, adding sugar gradually until well blended.
Add to Dream Whip and blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie filling and chill overnight.

title: crab soup
directions: Mix all together.
Do not add water with the soup!
Heat on warm.
Stir occasionally and then serve when the pea soup has melted.
Enjoy!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer hen or fryer with bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Pull meat off bones (skim off fat).
Melt fat in skillet; add chopped vegetables and cook until tender.
Add other seasonings, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chicken and simmer a few minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain (I cook it in my broth).
Put all ingredients in a casserole dish and add enough broth to make moist.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine, and salt in sauce pan. Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat add oatmeal, coconut, vanilla, and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients and cook 2 hours.
Makes 15 to 20 sandwiches.

title: crunchy curried chicken
directions: Place rice in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle chicken, ham and water chestnuts. Combine the next six ingredients. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake 5 minutes longer. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Make crust of graham crackers.
Mix lemon juice and condensed milk.
Gently fold in the blueberries.
Pour into pie shell. Top with whipped cream. Chill and serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook zucchini in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with cold water; let stand until cool enough to handle.
Carefully scoop out and save pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell of zucchini.
Chop pulp; combine with remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into zucchini shells.
Place in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soups in a large casserole pan.
Add green beans and mix well.
Top with sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Place in a hot greased skillet; sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind up peppers and onions; boil for about 30 minutes.
Pack in jars (6 1/2).

title: mocha mix
directions: Combine.
Store in container.
Use 4 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: a. l.'s fresh trout
directions: Preheat oil in frying pan to 350°.
Test temperature by dropping a small amount of water in oil to see if it pops.
Dredge trout in flour and dry, 2 pieces at a time, over medium flame, for 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
After all 6 pieces are fried, place on platter to keep warm.
Heat margarine with wine and pour over trout.
Garnish with lemon slices, garlic and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and Crisco until well blended and creamy. Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (do not open oven door for 1 hour).
Remove from pan when done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer in deep bowl in the order given. Cover airtight and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: baked rice and broccoli
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and stir until hot and well blended.
Add rice and broccoli and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: poor man pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; beat until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: farmhouse stew
directions: Crumble beef in a 3-quart microwave dish.
Add potatoes, cabbage, onion and celery.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients; cover and microwave 18 to 24 minutes. Serves 4 or 5.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables; salt to taste.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs with melted margarine; sprinkle over top.
Place under broiler until brown.

title: candy corn brittle
directions: Butter sides of a 3-quart heavy saucepan or Dutch oven. Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in pan.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium-low heat until sugar dissolves.
Using a pastry brush dipped in hot water, wash down any sugar crystals on sides of pan, making sure thermometer does not touch bottom of pan. Increase heat to medium and bring to a boil.
Do not stir while syrup is boiling.
Continue to cook until syrup reaches hard crack stage (approximately 300° to 310°) and turns light golden in color.
Test about 1/2 teaspoon syrup in ice water.
Syrup should form brittle threads in ice water and remain brittle when removed from the water.

title: red beans and rice cajun style
directions: Rinse beans twice.
Put in 4-quart heavy pot.
Add water, ham and sausage.
Put on medium heat.
Chop and add onions, celery and green onions.
Add thyme and bay leaves.
Reduce heat when it reaches boiling point and cover.
Stir every 20 to 30 minutes for 3 hours or until tender.
Mash 1/4 of the beans.
After cooking, taste and season with Tabasco sauce or cayenne pepper.
Ladle beans and sauce over rice to serve hot.

title: pecan spinach dip
directions: After spinach is cooked and well drained, place in towel and squeeze dry. Set spinach aside. In medium-size bowl, soften cream cheese. When creamy stir in sour cream. add dried beef which has been rinsed in warm water and drained. When well blended, add remaining ingredients. Serve hot or cold.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Lightly grease 5 (9-inch) pie plates.
Combine flour, shortening, butter, sugar and vinegar.
Cut with pastry blender until mealy.
Mix egg with water and salt.
Toss with fork.
Chill 15 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Prick bottom with fork, for baked pie crusts.
For others, fill with filling and bake according to directions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash well and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken in pot
directions: Cook chicken with lots of water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cool, skin and debone chicken.
Chop celery and onion and add to stock; boil about 10 minutes.
Add noodles and cook another 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients including chicken.
Cook another 10 minutes.
If needed, add chicken broth.
Do not add water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and cheese.
Add broccoli and mix well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crushed cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Drain pineapple.
Chop pecans.
Mix all ingredients, except for 1/2 of the pecans.
Form into ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: turkey hash au gratin
directions: In a medium skillet, over medium-high heat, combine turkey and onion. Cook 5 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink.
Add potato, breaking up larger pieces of potatoes with spoon, if necessary. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add salt and pepper.
Into 1-quart ovenproof casserole, lightly coated with vegetable cooking spray, bake turkey
mixture in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top casserole with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, water, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer until very tender, about 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf, puree smooth in blender.
Return to same pan; stir in milk and heat gently.
Season to taste with Worcestershire.
Pour into soup bowls and garnish with chives, parsley or dill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add beaten egg to milk and mix with yeast and sugar dissolved in water. Cut shortening into flour.
Mix flour and liquid to form soft dough.
Knead gently on well floured board. Roll about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with large biscuit cutter. Brush the top with melted shortening or butter.
Fold into pocketbook rolls.
Place on a greased baking pan.
Cover with towel and allow to rise for 2 to 4 hours at room temperature until about double in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white's chocolate fudge
directions: Put the chocolate over low heat and let melt.
Then add the sugar and milk.
Turn the heat up, a little at a time, stir to keep the candy from burning.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Set the pan in a large container of cold water.
(Mrs.
White said, the secret to good non-grainy fudge is to let it cool in a big pan of cold water before beating it, she sometimes used the sink.)
Then add butter and vanilla.
Beat it until it has cooled somewhat and ready to pour.
Pour it into an already prepared buttered dish.
Let it harden and cut into squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Then add flour and cream alternately.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add syrup and Hershey bars. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour in a greased tube pan.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: quiche
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Meanwhile, bake pie shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle onion and meat in pie shell. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs slightly, and add milk, salt and nutmeg.
Stir well.
Pour over ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until well browned and set.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk, banana and lemon juice.
Add vanilla.
Incorporate wet ingredients with dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan (large); spray with Pam and dust with flour.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 40 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cream and syrup.
Beat eggs and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: california garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange bread in single pieces on large baking sheet.
In bowl mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread generously on bread slices.
Bake until hot and slightly crisp, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Good with Italian dishes or barbecue.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and soda; add to creamed mixture, alternating with 1/2 cup lemonade concentrate.
Stir in lemon peel.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
Brush hot cookies with remaining lemonade concentrate the sprinkle with a little granulated sugar. Or, chill the dough, make balls and roll in coarse sugar, bake and glaze with concentrate.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: polish potato pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
Using large spoon, drop on hot frying pan and fry both sides in corn oil.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugars.
Add egg, then beat until creamy. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add the other ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Cook from 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Bring last 5 ingredients to a boil.
At full boil add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Drop on wax paper and cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: In 8-inch skillet, cook and stir meat until brown. Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour.
While sauce simmers, cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Serve sauce on hot spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 2 servings.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion.
Add meat and seasoning.
Brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Place in greased casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Mash potatoes.
Add milk, egg and seasonings.
Put in mounds over meat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan with meat sauce
directions: Prepare meat sauce.
Cut eggplant lengthwise into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Coat each slice with flour and shake off excess. Heat about 1/4 inch oil in a wide frying an over medium-high heat. Dip eggplant slices in egg mixture.
Drain briefly and cook without crowding.
Adding oil as needed, until browned and tender when pierced.
Drain, when browned, on paper towels.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine as listed and mix well.
Shape into small balls. Place on
ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. (May bake longer for crisper cookie.)

title: lemon and lime delight
directions: Mix lime jello, lemon jello and 2 cups boiling water together; cool.
Add remaining ingredients and let this stand in bowl of your choice in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.
An elegant salad.

title: orange-pineapple homemade sherbet
directions: Combine.
Pour ingredients in a freezer can, stir slightly and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix oil and vinegar.
Heat until hot.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients together and marinate 12 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic beef enchiladas
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, combine beef, onions and about 1/2 cup water; cook until onions are translucent.
Add flour and seasonings; mix well.
Stir in tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer about 15 minutes, until most of liquid is absorbed. Pour about 1 1/2 cups sauce into an ungreased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spread about 1/4 cup beef mixture down the center of each tortilla shell; top with 1 to 2 Tbsp. cheese.
Roll up tightly; place seam side down over sauce.
Repeat with each tortilla shell. Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Broil on LOW until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana chips
directions: Slice bananas; dip into lemon juice.
Place on greased cookie sheet in single layer.
Bake in a 175° oven for 2 or 3 hours, or until golden brown.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and olive in butter 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper, capers, sugar and salt to taste.
Add shrimp (3 ounces per person), cooked or raw.
If raw, cook until shrimp is pink.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetarian chopped liver *
directions: Saute onions in oil until deep brown.
Drain peas.
Grind walnuts in processor.
Add onions and process 1/2 minute more. Add peas and remaining ingredients and process with a few on-off bursts until combined and smooth.
Serves 8 appetizer portions on lettuce plates.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease and flour baking pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.

Wash blueberries and drain well. Coat blueberries with 1/4 cup of the flour. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs. Add remaining flour until well mixed. Gently stir in coated blueberries. Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place hamburger in bottom of casserole dish, then add 1 layer potatoes (sliced thin), 1 layer onions (sliced thin) and 1 layer Cheddar cheese.
Cover with 1 can of mushroom soup that has been mixed with 1/2 can of water.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Serve with shredded cheese and chips.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients as they are listed.
Bake in loaf pan (approximate size, 8 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch) at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: delicious chicken
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and garlic in cooking oil until onion is tender.
Stir in vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Grill chicken for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together; pour over first mixture.
Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; combine eggs, oil and mashed bananas; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth, fold in nuts.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer.
(For milder version, omit green chili peppers and cayenne pepper; reduce crushed red pepper by 1 tablespoon and hot chili powder by 1 tablespoon.)

title: soupy soup
directions: Fill large saucepan 1/2 full of water.
Add tomato sauce, potatoes, corn, carrots and green beans.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar, if you wish.
Cook on medium-high until potatoes are tender.
Serve with Hot Country Corn Bread.

title: cheese souffle pudding
directions: Butter bread.
Place in stack and cut into slices, then in cubes.
Place layer of bread in baking dish.
Add layer of grated cheese, another layer of bread cubes and another layer of cheese. Add eggs and milk, mixed well with seasonings.
Pour all over bread.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes. It rises high and fluffy.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and almond extract.
Blend.
Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Measure 1 1/2 cups batter, stir in chocolate syrup.
Spoon batters alternately into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: fresh corn bake
directions: Combine melted butter, flour, salt, pepper, milk and corn. Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: "kota me rizi" - easy chicken pilaf
directions: *Any cream soup will do.

title: holiday aroma
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or large pot.
Add enough water to fill the container.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer as long as desired.
This gives your home a wonderful aroma for a festive holiday party.
Do not drink!

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, beat well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add extract.
Cover and chill 1 hour (can be overnight).
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 3/4-inch round cookie cutter; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired. Yields 4 dozen.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: In large Tupperware bowl, combine oil, dill weed, garlic powder and package of dressing.
Add crackers and stir.
Cover and let set 24 hours, stirring or shaking occasionally.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add flour and beat well.
Bake in tube pan using Crisco to coat inside of pan.
Sprinkle with flour.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Serve with nacho chips.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients except oleo.
Mix well and form into 48 small balls. Brown in oleo.
Add water to simmer.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: strawberry and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Stir in strawberries until thawed.
Add bananas, pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until set.
Prepare cheesecake mix, using package directions. Beat until thick.
Spread over congealed gelatin layer.
Chill until set.
Spread remaining liquid gelatin mixture over top. Chill until set.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease tube cake pan with butter.
Place frozen rolls evenly in cake pan.
Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Add nuts and raisins, if desired. Pour dry pudding mix over rolls.
Let rise overnight, 8 to 10 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Pull apart to serve.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados to a smooth pulp.
Add remaining ingredients and serve accompanied by tortilla chips.

title: jello whipped salad
directions: Mix jello (allow for juice in pineapple).
Refrigerate until it starts to jell, then whip.
Whip the cream; add 3 tablespoons sugar and add to whipped jello.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and jell.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pepper, onions, cheese and pimento in a large bowl; toss lightly to mix.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce (Tabasco); add this to the chicken mixture (mix gently, but well).
Spoon into a 1 1/2 quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs and oleo.
Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: kugel(jewish dish)
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Melt margarine and add cottage cheese, beaten eggs, sour cream and powdered sugar.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Could sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Use a 9-inch pan.
Make a double crust.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on high for 4 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with whipped cream or cream cheese frosting.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream. Put in 1-quart mold.

title: white chili(serves 8)
directions: Combine beans, broth, garlic and 1/2 the onions in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until beans are soft, 3 hours or more, adding more broth if necessary.
In a skillet, saute remaining onions in oil until tender.
Add chilies and seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Add to bean mixture.
Add chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Ladle chili into soup bowls and top with grated cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine first four ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix, milk and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls to form 6 biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamed peas
directions: Cook peas in salted water until done.
Add flour to melted butter; mix until a smooth paste.
Stir flour mixture into peas, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add water chestnuts.
(May substitute drained, sliced mushrooms for chestnuts.)
Add basil. Stir until mixed.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese, soup and mushrooms.
Heat on low until cheese melts.
Serve with French bread.

title: hot chicken wings(appetizers)
directions: Mix together last three ingredients.
Pour over wings in ovenproof pan.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°, stirring often.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese and stir in the can of Ro-Tel.
May add hamburger or sausage.
Pour over nachos.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg, water, salt and lemon or brandy extract.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour over fruits and nuts.
Mix well and stir into batter.
Spray 2 loaf pans with vegetable cooking spray.
Fill with batter; press down.
Bake in very slow oven (275°) for 2 1/2 or 3 hours or until done.
(Place shallow pan of hot water on bottom of oven during baking.)
Cool; remove cake from pans.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds fruitcake.

title: strawberry pretzel surprise
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries; crush pretzels in bottom of pan. Pour melted butter over pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust clear to pan edges.
Mix Jell-O, hot water, pineapple juice, pineapple and strawberries until content is syrupy.
Pour over other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: smore pie
directions: In saucepan, place chocolate bar, milk and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Cool.
Fold 1 1/2 cups whipped cream into chocolate mix.
Spread thin layer of warm hot fudge in bottom of pie crust.
Gently spoon cooked mixture into crust.
Top with reserved whipped cream and garnish with chocolate syrup topping.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
Mix sugar and flour.
Stir into pineapple-cheese mixture. Put into casserole dish.

title: vegetable soup(low calorie)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water in large soup kettle.
Add tomato juice.
Add assorted vegetables and simmer slowly until vegetables are tender.
Stores well in refrigerator or freezer.

title: crabmeat remick
directions: Divide crabmeat into 6 portions and place in individual remekins.
(Use crab shells.)
Heat in 400 degree oven and top with strips of crisp bacon.
Blend together mustard, paprika, celery salt, and tabasco.	Add chili sauce and vinegar.
Mix well.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Spread sauce over warm crabmeat and heat under broiler.
Serves 6.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Put on heat first 4 ingredients, stir until well mixed; boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat; cool thoroughly, then beat until thick.
Add vanilla.
Do not stir while boiling.

title: instant luau leaf
directions: Break
corned
beef into pieces.
Place it in center of pan with drained spinach around it.
Pour enough coconut milk over it. Bake
in
a 360° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until hot.	Can be	done in microwave oven in microproof pan.
Heat until hot.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Stir together.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bishop's chocolate pie
directions: Mix puddings and milk together in a medium size bowl.
Add ice cream and mix.
Pour over crust.
Chill.
After chilled, spread Cool Whip over top of pudding.
Sprinkle with chocolate shavings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put onion, lemon juice and eggs in blender.
Zap it.
Mix liquid with salmon and bread crumbs.
Put in medium sized glass baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serve. Easy and tasty!

title: parmesan potato crisps
directions: Scrub potatoes and slice thinly.
Arrange potatoes in a thin layer in a lightly greased baking pan.
Brush with melted margarine.

title: grilled basil burgers
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 8 (3/4-inch) patties.
Grill on Webber kettle.
Low calorie.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Combine corn, corn meal, eggs, salt, baking soda, milk 1/3 cup melted butter, 1/2 of the cheese and all of the chilies.
Beat well.
Heat oven to 400°.
Put the 2 tablespoons butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, and leave in the oven until butter is melted. Pour the corn bread batter in the casserole; sprinkle the top with the remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes or until it tests done in the center.
Serves 8.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all
in
saucepan and boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Do not stir unnecessarily.
Place, uncovered, in a 400° oven to lightly brown top.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: lemony new potatoes
directions: In large saucepot heat 1 inch water to boiling.
Add potatoes. Cover and cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
When potatoes are done, turn off stove top.
Pour potatoes into colander to drain.
Pour potatoes into serving dish and cover with foil.
Place butter, lemon juice, chives and salt in skillet on stove top.
Just prior to serving, turn on heat and stir with mixing spoon until butter has melted.
Remove foil from potatoes, pour lemon butter over potatoes to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cottage cheese noodles
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Combine with all ingredients, except butter.
Place in greased round casserole and dot with the butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roast brisket of beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown brisket in fat well on both sides.
Slice onions in bottom of roasting pan.
Put brisket and water on top.
Place carrots around the meat.
Sprinkle the meat with garlic, salt, Season-All and flour.
Cover and roast for 3 1/2 hours.
One hour before removing from oven, place the whole potatoes around the meat in the pan.
When done, remove from pan to platter; place the carrots and potatoes around the slices of meat.
Spiced peaches make an excellent extra garnish.
